obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (101428)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101428&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Industrial Relations`
  line `Code, 2020.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall extend to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint; and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Code and`
  line `any reference in any such provision to the commencement of this Code shall be construed as a reference`
  line `to the coming into force of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 21st day of November, 2025---vide Notification No. S.O. 5320(E), dated 21st November, 2025, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (101429)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101429&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Code, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `(a) "appellate authority" means an authority appointed by the appropriate Government to`
  line `exercise such functions in such area as may be specified by that Government by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(b) "appropriate Government" means,---`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to any industrial establishment or undertaking carried on by or under the`
  line `authority of the Central Government or concerning any such controlled industry as may be`
  line `specified in this behalf by the Central Government or the establishment of railways including`
  line `metro railways, mines, oil fields, major ports, air transport service, telecommunication, banking`
  line `and insurance company or a corporation or other authority established by a Central Act or a`
  line `central public sector undertaking, subsidiary companies set up by the principal undertakings or`
  line `autonomous bodies owned or controlled by the Central Government including establishments`
  line `of the contractors for the purposes of such establishment, corporation, other authority, public`
  line `sector undertakings or any company in which not less than fifty-one per cent. of the paid-up`
  line `share capital is held by the Central Government, as the case may be, the Central Government.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this clause, the Central Government shall continue to`
  line `be the appropriate Government for central public sector undertakings even if the holding of the`
  line `Central Government reduces to less than fifty per cent. equity in that public sector undertaking`
  line `after the commencement of this Code;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to any other industrial establishment, including State public sector`
  line `undertakings, subsidiary companies set up by the principal undertaking and autonomous bodies`
  line `owned or controlled by the State Government, the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of a dispute between a contractor and the contract labour employed`
  line `through the contractor in any industrial establishment where such dispute first arose, the`
  line `appropriate Government shall be the Central Government or the State Government, as the case`
  line `may be, which has control over such industrial establishment;`
  line
  line `(c) "arbitrator" includes an umpire;`
  line
  line `(d) "average pay" means the average of the wages payable to a worker,---`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of monthly paid worker, in three complete calendar months;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of weekly paid worker, in four complete weeks;`
  line
  line `(iii) in the case of daily paid worker, in twelve full working days,`
  line
  line `preceding the date on which the average pay becomes payable, if the worker had worked for three`
  line `complete calendar months or four complete weeks or twelve full working days, as the case may be,`
  line `and where such calculation cannot be made, the average pay shall be calculated as the average of`
  line `the wages payable to a worker during the period he actually worked;`
  line
  line `(e) "award" means an interim or a final determination of any industrial dispute or of any`
  line `question relating thereto by any Industrial Tribunal referred to in section 44 or National Industrial`
  line `Tribunal referred to in section 46 and includes an arbitration award made under section 42;`
  line
  line `(f) "banking company" means a banking company as defined in section 5 of the Banking`
  line `Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949) and includes the Export-Import Bank of India, the Industrial`
  line `Reconstruction Bank of India, the Small Industries Development Bank of India established under`
  line `section 3 of the Small Industries Development Bank of India Act, 1989 (39 of 1989), the Reserve`
  line `Bank of India, the State Bank of India, a corresponding new bank constituted under section 3 of the`
  line `Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1970 (5 of 1970), a`
  line `corresponding new bank constituted under section 3 of the Banking Companies (Acquisition and`
  line `Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1980 (40 of 1980);`
  line
  line `(g) "certifying officer" means any officer appointed by the appropriate Government, by`
  line `notification, to perform the functions of a certifying officer under the provisions of Chapter IV;`
  line
  line `(h) "closure" means the permanent closing down of a place of employment or part thereof;`
  line
  line `(i) "conciliation officer" means a conciliation officer appointed under section 43;`
  line
  line `(j) "conciliation proceeding" means any proceeding held by a conciliation officer under this`
  line Code;
  line
  line `(k) "controlled industry" means any industry the control of which by the Union has been`
  line `declared by any Central Act to be expedient in the public interest;`
  line
  line `(l) "employee" means any person (other than an apprentice engaged under the Apprentices`
  line `Act, 1961) (52 of 1961) employed by an industrial establishment to do any skilled, semi-skilled or`
  line `unskilled, manual, operational, supervisory, managerial, administrative, technical or clerical work`
  line `for hire or reward, whether the terms of employment be express or implied, and also includes a`
  line `person declared to be an employee by the appropriate Government, but does not include any member`
  line `of the Armed Forces of the Union;`
  line
  line `(m) "employer" means a person who employs, whether directly or through any person, or on`
  line `his behalf or on behalf of any person, one or more employee or worker in his establishment and`
  line `where the establishment is carried on by any department of the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government, the authority specified by the head of the department in this behalf or where no`
  line `authority is so specified, the head of the department, and in relation to an establishment carried on`
  line `by a local authority, the chief executive of that authority, and includes,---`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to an establishment which is a factory, the occupier of the factory as defined`
  line `in clause (n) of section 2 of the Factories Act, 1948 (63 of 1948) and, where a person has been`
  line `named as a manager of the factory under clause (f) of sub-section (1) of section 7 of the said`
  line `Act, the person so named;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to any other establishment, the person who, or the authority which has`
  line `ultimate control over the affairs of the establishment and where the said affairs are entrusted`
  line `to a manager or managing director, such manager or managing director;`
  line
  line `(iii) contractor; and`
  line
  line `(iv) legal representative of a deceased employer;`
  line
  line `(n) "executive", in relation to a Trade Union, means the body by whatever name called, to`
  line `which the management of the affairs of a Trade Union is entrusted;`
  line
  line `(o) "fixed term employment" means the engagement of a worker on the basis of a written`
  line `contract of employment for a fixed period:`
  line
  line `Provided that---`
  line
  line `(a) his hours of work, wages, allowances and other benefits shall not be less than that of`
  line `a permanent worker doing the same work or work of similar nature;`
  line
  line `(b) he shall be eligible for all statutory benefits available to a permanent worker`
  line `proportionately according to the period of service rendered by him even if his period of`
  line `employment does not extend to the qualifying period of employment required in the statute;`
  line and
  line
  line `(c) he shall be eligible for gratuity if he renders service under the contract for a period of`
  line `one year;`
  line
  line `(p) "industry" means any systematic activity carried on by co-operation between an employer`
  line `and worker (whether such worker is employed by such employer directly or by or through any`
  line `agency, including a contractor) for the production, supply or distribution of goods or services with`
  line `a view to satisfy human wants or wishes (not being wants or wishes which are merely spiritual or`
  line `religious in nature), whether or not,---`
  line
  line `(i) any capital has been invested for the purpose of carrying on such activity; or`
  line
  line `(ii) such activity is carried on with a motive to make any gain or profit, but does not`
  line `include ---`
  line
  line `(i) institutions owned or managed by organisations wholly or substantially engaged`
  line `in any charitable, social or philanthropic service; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any activity of the appropriate Government relatable to the sovereign functions`
  line `of the appropriate Government including all the activities carried on by the departments`
  line `of the Central Government dealing with defence research, atomic energy and space; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any domestic service; or`
  line
  line `(iv) any other activity as may be notified by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(q) "industrial dispute" means any dispute or difference between employers and employers or`
  line `between employers and workers or between workers and workers which is connected with the`
  line `employment or non-employment or the terms of employment or with the conditions of labour, of`
  line `any person and includes any dispute or difference between an individual worker and an employer`
  line `connected with, or arising out of discharge, dismissal, retrenchment or termination of such worker;`
  line
  line `(r) "industrial establishment or undertaking" means an establishment or undertaking in which`
  line `any industry is carried on:`
  line
  line `Provided that where several activities are carried on in an establishment or undertaking and`
  line `only one or some of such activities is or are an industry or industries, then,---`
  line
  line `(i) if any unit of such establishment or undertaking carrying on any activity, being an`
  line `industry, is severable from the other unit or units of such establishment or undertaking which`
  line `is not carrying on or aiding the carrying on of any such activity, such unit shall be deemed to`
  line `be a separate industrial establishment or undertaking;`
  line
  line `(ii) if the predominant activity or each of the predominant activities carried on in such`
  line `establishment or undertaking or any unit thereof is an industry and the other activity or each`
  line `of the other activities carried on in such establishment or undertaking or unit thereof is not`
  line `severable from and is, for the purpose of carrying on, or aiding the carrying on of, such`
  line `predominant activity or activities, the entire establishment or undertaking or, as the case may`
  line `be, unit thereof shall be deemed to be an industrial establishment or undertaking;`
  line
  line `(s) "insurance company" means a company as defined in section 2 of the Insurance Act, 1938`
  line `(4 of 1938);`
  line
  line `(t) "lay-off" (with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions) means the failure,`
  line `refusal or inability of an employer on account of shortage of coal, power or raw materials or the`
  line `accumulation of stocks or the break-down of machinery or natural calamity or for any other`
  line `connected reason, to give employment to a worker whose name is borne on the muster rolls of his`
  line `industrial establishment and who has not been retrenched.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- Every worker whose name is borne on the muster rolls of the industrial`
  line `establishment and who presents himself for work at the establishment at the time appointed for the`
  line `purpose during normal working hours on any day and is not given employment by the employer`
  line `within two hours of his so presenting himself shall be deemed to have been laid-off for that day`
  line `within the meaning of this clause:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the worker, instead of being given employment at the commencement of any`
  line `shift for any day is asked to present himself for the purpose during the second half of the shift for`
  line `the day and is given employment then, he shall be deemed to have been laid-off only for one-half`
  line `of that day:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if he is not given any such employment even after so presenting himself,`
  line `he shall not be deemed to have been laid-off for the second half of the shift for the day and shall`
  line `be entitled to full basic wages and dearness allowance for that part of the day;`
  line
  line `(u) "lock-out" means the temporary closing of a place of employment, or the suspension of`
  line `work, or the refusal by an employer to continue to employ any number of persons employed by`
  line him;
  line
  line `(v) "major port" means a major port as defined in clause (8) of section 3 of the Indian Ports`
  line `Act, 1908 (15 of 1908);`
  line
  line `(w) "metro railway" means the metro railway as defined in sub-clause (i) of clause (1) of`
  line `section 2 of the Metro Railways (Operation and Maintenance) Act, 2002 (60 of 2002);`
  line
  line `(x) "mine" means a mine as defined in clause (j) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Mines`
  line `Act, 1952 (35 of 1952);`
  line
  line `(y) "National Industrial Tribunal" means a National Industrial Tribunal constituted under`
  line `section 46;`
  line
  line `(z) "negotiating union or negotiating council" means the negotiating union or negotiating`
  line `council referred to in section 14;`
  line
  line `(za) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette of India or the`
  line `Official Gazette of a State, as the case may be, and the expression "notify" with its grammatical`
  line `variation and cognate expressions shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(zb) "office-bearer", in relation to a Trade Union, includes any member of the executive`
  line `thereof, but does not include an auditor;`
  line
  line `(zc) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Code;`
  line
  line `(zd) "railway" means the railway as defined in clause (31) of section 2 of the Railways Act,`
  line `1989 (24 of 1989);`
  line
  line `(ze) "registered office" means that office of a Trade Union which is registered under this Code`
  line `as the head office thereof;`
  line
  line `(zf) "registered Trade Union" means a Trade Union registered under this Code;`
  line
  line `(zg) "Registrar" means a Registrar of Trade Unions appointed by the State Government under`
  line `section 5;`
  line
  line `(zh) "retrenchment" means the termination by the employer of the service of a worker for any`
  line `reason whatsoever, otherwise than as a punishment inflicted by way of disciplinary action, but`
  line `does not include---`
  line
  line `(i) voluntary retirement of the worker; or`
  line
  line `(ii) retirement of the worker on reaching the age of superannuation; or`
  line
  line `(iii) termination of the service of the worker as a result of the non-renewal of the`
  line `contract of employment between the employer and the worker concerned on its expiry or of`
  line `such contract being terminated under a stipulation in that behalf contained therein; or`
  line
  line `(iv) termination of service of the worker as a result of completion of tenure of fixed`
  line `term employment; or`
  line
  line `(v) termination of the service of a worker on the ground of continued ill-health;`
  line
  line `(zi) "settlement" means a settlement arrived at in the course of conciliation proceeding and`
  line `includes a written agreement between the employer and worker arrived at otherwise than in the`
  line `course of conciliation proceeding where such agreement has been signed by the parties thereto in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed and a copy thereof has been sent to an officer authorised in this`
  line `behalf by the appropriate Government and to the conciliation officer;`
  line
  line `(zj) "standing orders" means orders relating to matters set-out in the First Schedule;`
  line
  line `(zk) "strike" means a cessation of work by a body of persons employed in any industry acting`
  line `in combination, or a concerted refusal, or a refusal, under a common understanding, of any number`
  line `of persons who are or have been so employed to continue to work or to accept employment and`
  line `includes the concerted casual leave on a given day by fifty per cent. or more workers employed in`
  line `an industry;`
  line
  line `(zl) "Trade Union" means any combination, whether temporary or permanent, formed`
  line `primarily for the purpose of regulating the relations between workers and employers or between`
  line `workers and workers, or between employers and employers, or for imposing restrictive conditions`
  line `on the conduct of any trade or business, and includes any federation of two or more Trade Unions:`
  line
  line `Provided that the provisions of Chapter III of this Code shall not affect ---`
  line
  line `(i) any agreement between partners as to their own business; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any agreement between an employer and those employed by him as to such`
  line `employment; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any agreement in consideration of the sale of the goodwill of a business or of`
  line `instruction in any profession, trade or handicraft;`
  line
  line `(zm) "Trade Union dispute" means any dispute relating to Trade Union arising between two`
  line `or more Trade Unions or between the members of a Trade Union inter se;`
  line
  line `(zn) "Tribunal" means an Industrial Tribunal constituted under section 44;`
  line
  line `(zo) "unfair labour practice" means any of the practices specified in the Second Schedule;`
  line
  line `(zp) "unorganised sector" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (l) of section`
  line `2 of the Unorganised Workers' Social Security Act, 2008 (33 of 2008);`
  line
  line `(zq) "wages" means all remuneration, whether by way of salary, allowances or otherwise,`
  line `expressed in terms of money or capable of being so expressed which would, if the terms of`
  line `employment, express or implied, were fulfilled, be payable to a person employed in respect of his`
  line `employment or of work done in such employment, and includes,---`
  line
  line `(i) basic pay;`
  line
  line `(ii) dearness allowance;`
  line
  line `(iii) retaining allowance, if any,`
  line
  line `but does not include---`
  line
  line `(a) any bonus payable under any law for the time being in force, which does not form`
  line `part of the remuneration payable under the terms of employment;`
  line
  line `(b) the value of any house-accommodation, or of the supply of light, water, medical`
  line `attendance or other amenity or of any service excluded from the computation of wages by`
  line `a general or special order of the appropriate Government;`
  line
  line `(c) any contribution paid by the employer to any pension or provident fund, and the`
  line `interest which may have accrued thereon;`
  line
  line `(d) any conveyance allowance or the value of any travelling concession;`
  line
  line `(e) any sum paid to the employed person to defray special expenses entailed on him by`
  line `the nature of his employment;`
  line
  line `(f) house rent allowance;`
  line
  line `(g) remuneration payable under any award or settlement between the parties or order`
  line `of a court or Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(h) any overtime allowance;`
  line
  line `(i) any commission payable to the employee;`
  line
  line `(j) any gratuity payable on the termination of employment; or`
  line
  line `(k) any retrenchment compensation or other retirement benefit payable to the`
  line `employee or any ex gratia payment made to him on the termination of employment:`
  line
  line `Provided that, for calculating the wage under this clause, if any payments made by the`
  line `employer to the employee under sub-clauses (a) to (i) exceeds one-half, or such other per cent. as may be notified by the Central Government, of all remuneration calculated under this clause,`
  line `the amount which exceeds such one-half, or the per cent. so notified, shall be deemed to be`
  line `remuneration and shall be accordingly added in wages under this clause:`
  line
  line `Provided further that for the purpose of equal wages to all genders and for the purpose of`
  line `payment of wages the emoluments specified in sub-clauses (d), (f), (g) and (h) shall be taken for`
  line `computation of wage.`
  line
  line `Explanation. --- Where an employee is given in lieu of the whole or part of the wages`
  line `payable to him, any remuneration in kind by his employer, the value of such remuneration in`
  line `kind which does not exceed fifteen per cent. of the total wages payable to him, shall be deemed`
  line `to form part of the wages of such employee;`
  line
  line `(zr) "worker" means any person (except an apprentice as defined under clause (aa) of section`
  line `2 of the Apprentices Act, 1961) (52 of 1961) employed in any industry to do any manual, unskilled,`
  line `skilled, technical, operational, clerical or supervisory work for hire or reward, whether the terms`
  line `of employment be express or implied, and includes working journalists as defined in clause (f) of`
  line `section 2 of the Working Journalists and other Newspaper Employees (Conditions of Service) and`
  line `Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 195 (45 of 1955) 5 and sales promotion employees as defined in`
  line `clause (d) of section 2 of the Sales Promotion Employees (Conditions of Service) Act, 1976 (11 of`
  line `1976), and for the purposes of any proceeding under this Code in relation to an industrial dispute,`
  line `includes any such person who has been dismissed, discharged or retrenched or otherwise`
  line `terminated in connection with, or as a consequence of, that dispute, or whose dismissal, discharge`
  line `or retrenchment has led to that dispute, but does not include any such person---`
  line
  line `(i) who is subject to the Air Force Act, 1950 (45 of 1950), or the Army Act, 1950`
  line `(46 of 1950), or the Navy Act, 1957 (62 of 1957); or`
  line
  line `(ii) who is employed in the police service or as an officer or other employee of a prison;`
  line or
  line
  line `(iii) who is employed mainly in a managerial or administrative capacity; or`
  line
  line `(iv) who is employed in a supervisory capacity drawing wages exceeding eighteen`
  line `thousand rupees per month or an amount as may be notified by the Central Government from`
  line `time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that for the purposes of Chapter III, "worker"---`
  line
  line `(a) means all persons employed in trade or industry; and`
  line
  line `(b) includes the worker as defined in clause (m) of section 2 of the Unorganised Workers' Social`
  line `Security Act, 2008 (33 of 2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (101430)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Works Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101430&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the case of any industrial establishment in which one hundred or`
  line `more workers are employed or have been employed on any day in the preceding twelve months, the`
  line `appropriate Government may by general or special order require the employer to constitute a Works`
  line `Committee, in such manner as may be prescribed, consisting of representatives of employer and workers`
  line `engaged in the establishment:`
  line
  line `Provided that the number of representatives of workers in such Committee shall not be less than the`
  line `number of representatives of the employer.`
  line
  line `(2) The representatives of the workers shall be chosen, in such manner as may be prescribed, from`
  line `among the workers engaged in the establishment and in consultation with their Trade Union, if any,`
  line `registered in accordance with the provisions of section 9.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be the duty of the Works Committee to promote measures for securing and preserving`
  line `amity and good relations between the employer and workers and, to that end, to comment upon matters`
  line `of their common interest or concern and endeavour to compose any material difference of opinion in`
  line `respect of such matters.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (101431)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Grievance Redressal Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101431&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every industrial establishment employing twenty or`
  line `more workers shall have one or more Grievance Redressal Committees for resolution of disputes arising`
  line `out of individual grievances.`
  line
  line `(2) The Grievance Redressal Committee shall consist of equal number of members representing the`
  line `employer and the workers to be chosen in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The chairperson of the Grievance Redressal Committee shall be selected from among persons`
  line `representing the employer and the workers alternatively on rotational basis every year.`
  line
  line `(4) The total number of members of the Grievance Redressal Committee shall not exceed ten:`
  line `Provided that there shall be adequate representation of women workers in the Grievance Redressal`
  line `Committee and such representation shall not be less than the proportion of women workers to the total`
  line `workers employed in the industrial establishment.`
  line
  line `(5) An application in respect of any dispute referred to in sub-section (1) may be filed before the`
  line `Grievance Redressal Committee by any aggrieved worker in such manner as may be prescribed within`
  line `one year from the date on which the cause of action of such dispute arises.`
  line
  line `(6) The Grievance Redressal Committee may complete its proceedings within thirty days of receipt`
  line `of the application under sub-section (5).`
  line
  line `(7) The decision of the Grievance Redressal Committee on any application filed under`
  line `sub-section (5) shall be made on the basis of majority view of the Committee, provided more than half`
  line `of the members representing the workers have agreed to such decision, otherwise it shall be deemed`
  line `that no decision could be arrived at by the Committee.`
  line
  line `(8) The worker who is aggrieved by the decision of the Grievance Redressal Committee or whose`
  line `grievance is not resolved in the said Committee within the period specified in sub-section (6), may,`
  line `within a period of sixty days from the date of the decision of the Grievance Redressal Committee or`
  line `from the date on which the period specified in sub-section (6) expires, as the case may be, file an`
  line `application for the conciliation of such grievance to the conciliation officer through the Trade Union,`
  line `of which he is a member, in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(9) Where any employer discharges, dismisses, retrenches, or otherwise terminates the services of`
  line `an individual worker, any dispute or difference between that worker and his employer connected with,`
  line `or arising out of, such discharge, dismissal, retrenchment or termination shall be deemed to be an`
  line `industrial dispute notwithstanding that no other worker nor any Trade Union is a party to the dispute.`
  line
  line `(10) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section or section 53, any worker as is specified in`
  line `sub-section (5) may, make an application directly to the Tribunal for adjudication of the dispute referred`
  line `to therein after the expiry of forty-five days from the date he has made the application to the conciliation`
  line `officer of the appropriate Government for conciliation of the dispute, and on receipt of such application`
  line `the Tribunal shall have powers and jurisdiction to adjudicate upon the dispute, as the Tribunal has in`
  line `respect of the application filed under sub-section (6) of section 53.`
  line
  line `(11) The application referred to in sub-section (10) shall be made to the Tribunal before the expiry`
  line `of two years from the date of discharge, dismissal, retrenchment or otherwise termination of service as`
  line `specified in sub-section (9).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (101432)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Registrar of Trade Unions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101432&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification, appoint a person`
  line `to be the Registrar of Trade Unions, and other persons as Additional Registrar of Trade Unions, Joint`
  line `Registrar of Trade Unions and Deputy Registrar of Trade Unions, who shall exercise such powers and`
  line `perform such duties of the Registrar as the State Government may, by notification, specify from time`
  line `to time.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of any order made by the State Government, where an Additional`
  line `Registrar of Trade Unions or a Joint Registrar of Trade Unions or a Deputy Registrar of Trade Unions`
  line `exercises the powers and performs the duties of the Registrar in an area within which the registered`
  line `office of a Trade Union is situated, such Additional Registrar of Trade Unions or a Joint Registrar of`
  line `Trade Unions or a Deputy Registrar of Trade Unions, as the case may be, shall be deemed to be the`
  line `Registrar in relation to that Trade Union for the purposes of this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (101433)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Criteria for registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101433&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any seven or more members of a Trade Union may, by`
  line `subscribing their names to the rules of the Trade Union and by otherwise complying with the provisions`
  line `of this Code with respect to registration, apply for registration of the Trade Union under this Code.`
  line
  line `(2) No Trade Union of workers shall be registered unless at least ten per cent. of the workers or one`
  line `hundred workers, whichever is less, engaged or employed in the industrial establishment or industry`
  line `with which it is connected are the members of such Trade Union on the date of making of application`
  line `for registration.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an application has been made under sub-section (1) for registration of a Trade Union,`
  line `such application shall not be deemed to have become invalid merely by reason of the fact that, at any`
  line `time after the date of the application but before the registration of the Trade Union, some of the`
  line `applicants, but not exceeding half of the total number of persons who made the application, have ceased`
  line `to be members of the Trade Union or have given notice in writing to the Registrar dissociating`
  line `themselves from the application.`
  line
  line `(4) A registered Trade Union of workers shall at all times continue to have not less than ten per cent.`
  line `of the workers or one hundred workers, whichever is less, subject to a minimum of seven, engaged or`
  line `employed in an industrial establishment or industry with which it is connected, as its members.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (101434)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Provisions to be contained in constitution or rules of Trade Union.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101434&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `A Trade Union shall not`
  line `be entitled to registration under this Code, unless the executive thereof is constituted in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of this Code, and the rules of the Trade Union provide for the following matters,`
  line `namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the name of the Trade Union;`
  line
  line `(b) the whole of the objects for which the Trade Union has been established;`
  line
  line `(c) the whole of the purposes for which the general funds of the Trade Union shall be applicable,`
  line `all of which purposes shall be purposes to which such funds are lawfully applicable under this Code;`
  line
  line `(d) the maintenance of a list of members of the Trade Union and adequate facilities for the`
  line `inspection thereof by the office-bearers and members of the Trade Union;`
  line
  line `(e) the admission of ordinary members (irrespective of their craft or category) who shall be`
  line `persons actually engaged or employed in the industrial establishment, undertaking or industry, or`
  line `units, branches or offices of an industrial establishment, as the case may be, with which the Trade`
  line `Union is connected, and also the admission of such number of honorary or temporary members, who`
  line `are not such workers, as are not permitted under section 21 to be office-bearers to form the executive`
  line `of the Trade Union;`
  line
  line `(f) the payment of a subscription by members of the Trade Union from such members and`
  line `others, as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(g) the conditions under which any member shall be entitled to any benefit assured by the rules`
  line `and under which any fine or forfeiture may be imposed on any member;`
  line
  line `(h) the annual general body meeting of the members of the Trade Union, the business to be`
  line `transacted at such meeting, including the election of office-bearers of the Trade Union;`
  line
  line `(i) the manner in which the members of the executive and the other office bearers of the Trade`
  line `Union shall be elected once in a period of every three years and removed, and filling of casual`
  line vacancies;
  line
  line `(j) the safe custody of the funds of the Trade Union, an annual audit, in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed, of the accounts thereof, and adequate facilities for the inspection of the account books`
  line `by the office-bearers and members of the Trade Union;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner in which the rules shall be amended, varied or rescinded; and`
  line
  line `(l) the manner in which the Trade Union may be dissolved.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (101435)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Application for registration, alteration of name and procedure thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101435&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every`
  line `application for registration of a Trade Union shall be made to the Registrar electronically or otherwise`
  line `and be accompanied by---`
  line
  line `(a) a declaration to be made by an affidavit in such form and manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) copy of the rules of the Trade Union together with a copy of the resolution by the members`
  line `of the Trade Union adopting such rules;`
  line
  line `(c) a copy of the resolution adopted by the members of the Trade Union authorising the`
  line `applicants to make an application for registration; and`
  line
  line `(d) in the case of a Trade Union, being a federation or a central organisation of Trade Unions,`
  line `a copy of the resolution adopted by the members of each of the member Trade Unions, meeting`
  line `separately, agreeing to constitute a federation or a central organisation of Trade Unions.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this clause, resolution adopted by the members of the Trade`
  line `Union means, in the case of a Trade Union, being a federation or a central organisation of Trade`
  line `Unions, the resolution adopted by the members of each of the member Trade Unions, meeting`
  line separately.
  line
  line `(2) Where a Trade Union has been in existence for more than one year before the making of an`
  line `application for its registration, there shall be delivered to the Registrar, together with the application, a`
  line `general statement of the assets and liabilities of the Trade Union prepared in such form and containing`
  line `such particulars, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registrar may call for further information for the purpose of satisfying himself that the`
  line `application complies with the provisions of this Code and the Trade Union is entitled for registration`
  line `under this Code, and may refuse to register the Trade Union until such information is furnished.`
  line
  line `(4) If the name under which the Trade Union is proposed to be registered is identical with that of an`
  line `existing registered Trade Union or in the opinion of the Registrar so nearly resembles the name of an`
  line `existing Trade Union that such name is likely to deceive the public or the members of either Trade`
  line `Union, the Registrar shall require the persons applying for altering the name of the Trade Union and`
  line `shall refuse to register the Trade Union until such alteration has been made.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (101436)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Registration of Trade Union and cancellation thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101436&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar shall, on being`
  line `satisfied that the Trade Union has complied with all the requirements of the provisions of this Chapter`
  line `in regard to registration, register the Trade Union by entering in a register, to be maintained in such`
  line `form as may be prescribed, the particulars relating to the Trade Union contained in the statement`
  line `accompanying the application for registration.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Registrar makes an order for registration of a Trade Union, he shall issue a certificate`
  line `of registration to the applicant Trade Union, in such form as may be prescribed, which shall be the`
  line `conclusive evidence that the Trade Union has been registered under this Code.`
  line
  line `(3) If the Registrar has issued a certificate of registration to a Trade Union, he shall enter the name`
  line `and other particulars of the Trade Union in a register maintained in this behalf in such form as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(4) Every Trade Union registered under the Trade Unions Act, 1926 having valid registration`
  line `immediately before the commencement of this Code shall be deemed to have been registered under this`
  line `Code:`
  line
  line `Provided that such Trade Union shall file with the Registrar a statement that the constitution of the`
  line `executive of the Trade Union is in accordance with this Code along with the rules of the Trade Union`
  line `updated in accordance with section 7, and the Registrar shall amend his records accordingly.`
  line
  line `(5) The certificate of registration of a Trade Union may be withdrawn or cancelled by the`
  line Registrar,---
  line
  line `(i) on the application of the Trade Union verified in such manner as may be prescribed; or`
  line
  line `(ii) on the information received by him regarding the contravention by the Trade Union of the`
  line `provisions of this Code or the rules made thereunder or its constitution or rules; or`
  line
  line `(iii) if he is satisfied that the members in a Trade Union falls below ten per cent. of total workers`
  line `or one hundred workers, whichever is less:`
  line
  line `Provided that not less than sixty days previous notice in writing specifying the grounds on which it`
  line `is proposed to cancel the certificate of registration of a Trade Union shall be given by the Registrar to`
  line `the Trade Union before the certificate of registration is cancelled otherwise than on the application of`
  line `the Trade Union.`
  line
  line `(6) A certificate of registration of a Trade Union shall be cancelled by the Registrar where a Tribunal`
  line `has made an order for cancellation of registration of such Trade Union.`
  line
  line `(7) While cancelling the certificate of registration of a Trade Union, the Registrar shall record the`
  line `reasons for doing so and communicate the same in writing to the Trade Union concerned.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (101437)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Appeal against non-registration or cancellation of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101437&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved`
  line `by the refusal of the Registrar to grant registration to a Trade Union under section 9 or by cancellation`
  line `of a certificate of registration under sub-section (5) of the said section, may within such period as may`
  line `be prescribed, prefer an appeal to the Tribunal:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Tribunal may entertain the appeal after the limitation prescribed for preferring the`
  line `appeal under this sub-section, if the appellant satisfies the Tribunal that such delay has been caused due`
  line `to sufficient reason or unavoidable circumstances.`
  line
  line `(2) The Tribunal may, after giving the parties concerned an opportunity of being heard, dismiss the`
  line `appeal or pass an order directing the Registrar to register the Trade Union and to issue a certificate of`
  line `registration or set aside the order of cancellation of certificate of registration, as the case may be and`
  line `forward a copy of such order to the Registrar.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (101438)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Communication to Trade Union and change in its registration particulars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101438&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) All`
  line `communications and notices to a registered Trade Union shall be sent, in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed, to the address of the head office of the Trade Union as entered in the register maintained by`
  line `the Registrar.`
  line
  line `(2) The Trade Union shall inform the Registrar if the members of such Trade Union falls below ten`
  line `per cent. of total workers or one hundred workers, whichever is less.`
  line
  line `(3) The Trade Union shall inform the Registrar of any change in the particulars given by it in its`
  line `application for registration and in its constitution or rules, in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (101439)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Incorporation of a registered Trade Union.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101439&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Every registered Trade Union shall be a body`
  line `corporate by the name under which it is registered, and shall have perpetual succession and a common`
  line `seal with power to acquire and hold both movable and immovable property and to contract, and shall`
  line `by the said name sue and be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (101440)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Certain Acts not to apply to registered Trade Unions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101440&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of the following Acts,`
  line `namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860);`
  line
  line `(b) the Co-operative Societies Act, 1912 (2 of 1912);`
  line
  line `(c) the Multi-State Co-operative Societies Act, 2002 (39 of 2002);`
  line
  line `(d) the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013); and`
  line
  line `(e) any other corresponding law relating to co-operative societies for the time being in force`
  line `in any State,`
  line
  line `shall not apply to any registered Trade Union and the registration of any such Trade Union under any`
  line `of the aforementioned Acts shall be void.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (101441)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Recognition of negotiating union or negotiating council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101441&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a negotiating`
  line `union or a negotiating council, as the case may be, in an industrial establishment having registered`
  line `Trade Union for negotiating with the employer of the industrial establishment, on such matters as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Where only one Trade Union of workers registered under the provisions of this Chapter is`
  line `functioning in an industrial establishment, then, the employer of such industrial establishment shall,`
  line `subject to such criteria as may be prescribed, recognise such Trade Union as sole negotiating union of`
  line `the workers.`
  line
  line `(3) If more than one Trade Union of workers registered under this Code are functioning in an`
  line `industrial establishment, then, the Trade Union having fifty-one per cent. or more workers on the muster`
  line `roll of that industrial establishment, verified in such manner as may be prescribed, supporting that Trade`
  line `Union shall be recognised by the employer of the industrial establishment, as the sole negotiating union`
  line `of the workers.`
  line
  line `(4) If more than one Trade Union of workers registered under this Code are functioning in an`
  line `industrial establishment, and no such Trade Union has fifty-one per cent. or more of workers on the`
  line `muster roll of that industrial establishment, verified in such manner as may be prescribed, supporting`
  line `that Trade union, then, there shall be constituted by the employer of the industrial establishment, a`
  line `negotiating council for negotiation on the matters referred to in sub-section (1), consisting of the`
  line `representatives of such registered Trade Unions which have the support of not less than twenty per cent.`
  line `of the total workers on the muster roll of that industrial establishment so verified and such representation`
  line `shall be of one representative for each twenty per cent. and for the remainder after calculating the`
  line `membership on each twenty per cent.`
  line
  line `(5) Where any negotiation on the matters referred to in sub-section (1) is held between an employer`
  line `and a negotiating council constituted under sub-section (4), consequent upon such negotiation, any`
  line `agreement is said to be reached, if it is agreed by the majority of the representatives of the Trade Unions`
  line `in such negotiating council.`
  line
  line `(6) Any recognition made under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) or the negotiating council`
  line `constituted under sub-section (4) shall be valid for three years from the date of recognition or`
  line `constitution or such further period not exceeding five years, in total, as may be mutually decided by the`
  line `employer and the Trade Union, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(7) The facilities to be provided by industrial establishment to a negotiating union or negotiating`
  line `council shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (102033)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Objects of general fund, composition of separate fund and membership fee of Trade Union.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=102033&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The general funds of a registered Trade Union shall not be spent on any objects other than`
  line `such objects as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) A registered Trade Union may constitute a separate fund, from contributions separately levied`
  line `for or made to that fund, from which payments may be made, for the promotion of the civic and political`
  line `interests of its members, in furtherance of such objects as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) No member shall be compelled to contribute to the fund constituted under sub-section (2) and a`
  line `member who does not contribute to the said fund shall not be excluded from any benefits of the Trade`
  line `Union, or placed in any respect either directly or indirectly under any disability or at any disadvantage`
  line `as compared with other members of the Trade Union (except in relation to the control or management`
  line `of the said fund) by reason of his not contributing to the said fund; and contribution to the said fund`
  line `shall not be made a condition for admission to the Trade Union.`
  line
  line `(4) The subscriptions payable by the members of the Trade Union shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (101443)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Immunity from civil suit in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101443&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit or other legal proceeding shall be`
  line `maintainable in any civil court against any registered Trade Union or any office-bearer or member`
  line `thereof in respect of any act done in contemplation or furtherance of an industrial dispute to which a`
  line `member of the Trade Union is a party on the ground only that such act induces some other person to`
  line `break a contract of employment or that it is an interference with the trade, business, or employment of`
  line `some other person or with the right of some other person to dispose of his capital or of his labour as he`
  line wills.
  line
  line `(2) A registered Trade Union shall not be liable in any suit or other legal proceeding in any civil`
  line `court in respect of any tortuous act done in contemplation or furtherance of an industrial dispute by an`
  line `agent of the Trade Union if it is proved that such person acted without the knowledge of, or contrary to`
  line `express instructions given by, the executive of the Trade Union.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (101444)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Criminal conspiracy in furtherance of objects of Trade Union.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101444&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `No office-bearer or member`
  line `of a registered Trade Union shall be liable to punishment under sub-section (2) of section 120B of the`
  line `Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) in respect of any agreement made between the members for the purpose`
  line `of furthering any such object of the Trade Union as is specified in section 15, unless such agreement is`
  line `an agreement to commit an offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (101445)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Enforceability of agreements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101445&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the`
  line `time being in force, an agreement between the members of a registered Trade Union shall not be void`
  line `or voidable merely by reason of the fact that any of the objects of the agreement are in restraint of trade:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall enable any civil court to entertain any legal proceedings`
  line `instituted for the purpose of enforcing or recovering damages for the breach of any agreement`
  line `concerning the conditions on which any members of a Trade Union shall or shall not sell their goods,`
  line `transact business, work, employ or be employed.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (101446)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Right to inspect books of Trade Union.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101446&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The books of account of a registered Trade Union`
  line `and the list of members thereof shall be open to inspection by an office-bearer or member of the Trade`
  line `Union at such times as may be provided for in the rules of the Trade Union.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (101447)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Rights of minor to membership of Trade Union.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101447&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Any person who has attained the age of`
  line `fourteen years and is employed in a nonhazardous industry may be a member of a registered Trade`
  line `Union subject to any rules of the Trade Union, and may, subject to as aforesaid enjoy all the rights of a`
  line `member and execute all instruments and given all acquaintances necessary to be executed or given`
  line `under the rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (101448)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Disqualification of office-bearers of Trade Unions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101448&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall be disqualified for`
  line `being chosen as, and for being, a member of the executive or any other office-bearer of a registered`
  line `Trade Union, if---`
  line
  line `(i) he has not attained the age of eighteen years;`
  line
  line `(ii) he has been convicted by a court in India for any offence involving moral turpitude and`
  line `sentenced to imprisonment unless a period of five years has elapsed since his release;`
  line
  line `(iii) the Tribunal has directed that he shall be disqualified for being chosen or for being office-bearer of a Trade Union for a period specified therein.`
  line
  line `(2) No member of the Council of Ministers or a person holding an office of profit (not being an`
  line `engagement or employment in an establishment or industry with which the Trade Union is connected)`
  line `in the Union or a State shall be a member of the executive or other office-bearer of a Trade Union.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (101449)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Adjudication of disputes of Trade Unions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101449&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a dispute arises between---`
  line
  line `(a) one Trade Union and another; or`
  line
  line `(b) one or more workers who are members of the Trade Union and the Trade Union regarding`
  line `registration, administration or management or election of office-bearers of the Trade Union; or`
  line
  line `(c) one or more workers who are refused admission as members and the Trade Union; or`
  line
  line `(d) where a dispute is in respect of a Trade Union which is a federation of Trade Unions and`
  line `office-bearer authorised in this behalf by the Trade Union,`
  line
  line `an application may be made in such manner as may be prescribed to the Tribunal having jurisdiction`
  line `over the area where the registered office of the Trade Union or Trade Unions is located for adjudication`
  line `of such disputes.`
  line
  line `(2) No civil court other than the Tribunal shall have power to entertain any suit or other proceedings`
  line `in relation to any dispute referred to in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (101450)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Proportion of office-bearers to be connected with industry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101450&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Not less than one-half of`
  line `the total number of the office-bearers of every registered Trade Union in an unorganised sector shall be`
  line `persons actually engaged or employed in an establishment or industry with which the Trade Union is`
  line `connected:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appropriate Government may, by special or general order, declare that the`
  line `provisions of this section shall not apply to any Trade Union or class of Trade Unions specified in the`
  line order.
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this sub-section, "unorganised sector" means any sector which`
  line `the appropriate Government may, by notification, specify.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (1), all office-bearers of a registered Trade Union,`
  line `except not more than one-third of the total number of the office-bearers or five, whichever is less, shall`
  line `be persons actually engaged or employed in the establishment or industry with which the Trade Union`
  line `is connected.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this sub-section, an employee who has retired or has been`
  line `retrenched shall not be construed as outsider for the purpose of holding an office in a Trade Union.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (101451)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Change of name, amalgamation, notice of change and its effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101451&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any registered Trade`
  line `Union may, with the consent of not less than two-third of the total number of its members and subject`
  line `to the provisions of sub-section (3), change its name.`
  line
  line `(2) Any two or more registered Trade Unions may be amalgamated in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) Notice in writing of every change of name and of every amalgamation signed in the case of a`
  line `change of name, by the secretary and by seven members of the Trade Union changing its name, and in`
  line `the case of an amalgamation, by the secretary and by seven members of each and every Trade Union`
  line `which is a party thereto, shall be sent to the Registrar and where the head office of the amalgamated`
  line `Trade Union is situated in a different State, to the Registrar of such State in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(4) If the proposed name is identical with that by which any other existing Trade Union has been`
  line `registered or, in the opinion of the Registrar, so nearly resembles such name as to be likely to deceive`
  line `the public or the members of either Trade Union, the Registrar shall refuse to register the change of`
  line name.
  line
  line `(5) Save as provided in sub-section (4), the Registrar shall, if he is satisfied that the provisions of`
  line `this Code in respect of change of name have been complied with, register the change of name in the`
  line `register referred to in sub-section (3) of section 9, and the change of name shall have effect from the`
  line `date of such registration.`
  line
  line `(6) The Registrar of the State in which the head office of the amalgamated Trade Union is situated`
  line `shall, if he is satisfied that the provisions of this Code in respect of amalgamation have been complied`
  line `with and that the Trade Union formed thereby is entitled to registration under section 9, register the`
  line `Trade Union and the amalgamation shall have effect from the date of such registration.`
  line
  line `(7) The change in the name of a registered Trade Union shall not affect any rights or obligations of`
  line `the Trade Union or render defective any legal proceeding by or against the Trade Union, and any legal`
  line `proceeding which might have been continued or commenced by or against it by its former name may`
  line `be continued or commenced by or against it by its new name.`
  line
  line `(8) An amalgamation of two or more registered Trade Unions shall not prejudice any right of any`
  line `such Trade Unions or any right of a creditor of any of them.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (101452)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title Dissolution.
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101452&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a registered Trade Union is dissolved, notice of the dissolution signed`
  line `by seven members and by the secretary of the Trade Union shall, within fourteen days of the dissolution,`
  line `be sent to the Registrar, and shall be registered by him if he is satisfied that the dissolution has been`
  line `effected in accordance with the rules of the Trade Union, and the dissolution shall have effect from the`
  line `date of such registration.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the dissolution of a registered Trade Union has been registered and the rules of the Trade`
  line `Union do not provide for the distribution of funds of the Trade Union on dissolution, the Registrar shall`
  line `divide the funds amongst the members in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (101453)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Annual returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101453&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every registered Trade Union shall---`
  line
  line `(a) forward annually to the Registrar, on or before such date, in such form, audited in such`
  line `manner and by such person, as may be prescribed, a general statement containing particulars of all`
  line `receipts and expenditure of such registered Trade Union during the year ending on the 31st day of`
  line `December next preceding such prescribed date, and of the assets and liabilities of the Trade Union`
  line `existing on such 31st day of December;`
  line
  line `(b) along with the general statement referred to in clause (a), forward to the Registrar a`
  line `statement showing changes of office-bearers made by the Trade Union during the year to which such`
  line `general statement refers, together also with a copy of the rules of the Trade Union corrected up to`
  line `the date of dispatch thereof to the Registrar.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every alteration made in the rules of a registered Trade Union shall be sent to the`
  line `Registrar within fifteen days of the making of the alteration.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purpose of examining the documents referred to in clauses (a) and (b) of sub-section (1),`
  line `and sub-section (2), the Registrar or any officer authorised by him, by general or special order, may at`
  line `all reasonable times inspect the certificate of registration, account books, registers and other documents,`
  line `relating to a Trade Union, at its registered office or may require their production at such place as he`
  line `may specify in this behalf, but no such place shall be at a distance of more than fifteen kilometres from`
  line `the registered office of such Trade Union.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (101454)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Recognition of Trade Unions at Central and State level.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101454&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Central Government`
  line `is of the opinion that it is necessary or expedient that a Trade Union or federation of Trade Unions is to`
  line `be recognised as Central Trade Union at the Central level, it may recognise such Trade Union or`
  line `federation of Trade Unions as Central Trade Union in such manner and for such purpose, as may be`
  line `prescribed, and if any dispute arises in relation to such recognition, it shall be decided by such authority`
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the State Government is of the opinion that it is necessary or expedient that a Trade Union`
  line `or federation of Trade Unions is to be recognised as State Trade Union at the State level, it may`
  line `recognise such Trade Union or federation of Trade Unions as State Trade Union in such manner and`
  line `for such purpose, as may be prescribed, and if any dispute arises in relation to such recognition, it shall`
  line `be decided by such authority in such manner as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (101455)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Application of this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101455&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Chapter shall apply to every industrial`
  line `establishment wherein three hundred or more than three hundred workers, are employed, or were`
  line `employed on any day of the preceding twelve months.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the provisions of this Chapter shall not`
  line `apply to an industrial establishment in so far as the workers employed therein are persons to whom the`
  line `Fundamental and Supplementary Rules, Civil Services (Classification, Control and Appeal) Rules,`
  line `Civil Services (Temporary Service) Rules, Revised Leave Rules, Civil Service Regulations, Civilians`
  line `in Defence Service (Classification, Control and Appeal) Rules or the Indian Railway Establishment`
  line `Code or any other rules or regulations that may be notified in this behalf by the appropriate Government,`
  line apply.
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (101456)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Making of model standing orders by Central Government and temporary application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101456&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall make model standing orders relating to conditions of service and`
  line `other matters incidental thereto or connected therewith.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sections 30 to 36, for the period commencing on the date`
  line `on which this section becomes applicable to an industrial establishment and ending with the date on`
  line `which the standing orders as finally certified under this Code come into operation under section 33 in`
  line `that establishment, the model standing order referred to in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to be adopted`
  line `in that establishment and the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 33 and section 35 shall apply to`
  line `such model standing orders as they apply to the standing orders so certified.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (101457)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Preparation of draft standing orders by employer and procedure for certification.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101457&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `employer shall prepare draft standing orders, within a period of six months from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Code, based on the model standing orders referred to in section 29 in respect of`
  line `the matters specified in the First Schedule and on any other matter considered necessary by him for`
  line `incorporation of necessary provisions in such standing orders for his industrial establishment or`
  line `undertaking, considering the nature of activity in his industrial establishment or undertaking, provided`
  line `such provision is not inconsistent with any of the provision of this Code and covers every matters set`
  line `out in the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) The employer shall consult the Trade Unions or recognised negotiating union or members of the`
  line `negotiating council relating to the industrial establishment or undertaking, as the case may be, in respect`
  line `of the draft of the standing order and thereafter forward the draft of the standing order electronically or`
  line `otherwise to the certifying officer for certification.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an employer adopts a model standing order of the Central Government referred to in`
  line `section 29 with respect to matters relevant to his industrial establishment or undertaking, then, such`
  line `model standing order shall be deemed to have been certified under the provisions of this section and`
  line `employer shall forward the information in this regard to the concerned certifying officer in such manner`
  line `as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the certifying officer has any observation, he may direct such employer to amend`
  line `the standing order so adopted within such period as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The employer shall prepare the draft of the modifications required in the standing order, if any,`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of this Code and forward electronically or otherwise to the certifying`
  line `officer for certification of those modifications only within a period of six months from the date, the`
  line `provisions of this Chapter becomes applicable to his industrial establishment.`
  line
  line `(5) On receipt of the drafts referred to in sub-section (1) and sub-section (4), the certifying officer`
  line `shall issue notice to---`
  line
  line `(i) the Trade Union or negotiating union of the industrial establishment or undertaking, or`
  line `members of the negotiating council; or`
  line
  line `(ii) where there is no Trade Union operating, to such representatives of the workers of the`
  line `industrial establishment or undertaking chosen in such manner as may be prescribed,`
  line
  line `for seeking their comments in the matter and after receipt of their comments give an opportunity of`
  line `being heard to the negotiating union or negotiating council, or as the case may be, to the Trade Unions`
  line `or the representatives of the workers and decide as to whether or not any modification or addition to`
  line `such draft standing order is necessary to render the draft standing order certifiable, and shall make an`
  line `order in writing in this regard:`
  line
  line `Provided that the certifying officer shall complete such procedure for certification referred to in subsections (4) and (5) in respect of---`
  line
  line `(a) the draft standing order so received within a period of sixty days from the date of the receipt`
  line `of it; and`
  line
  line `(b) the draft modifications in the standing order so received within a period of sixty days from`
  line `the date of the receipt of such modifications,`
  line
  line `failing which such draft standing orders or, as the case may be, the modifications in the standing order`
  line `shall be deemed to have been certified on the expiry of the said period.`
  line
  line `(6) The standing orders shall be certifiable under this Code, if---`
  line
  line `(a) provision is made therein for every matter set out in the First Schedule which is applicable`
  line `to the industrial establishment; and`
  line
  line `(b) such orders are otherwise in conformity with the provisions of this Code.`
  line
  line `(7) It shall be the function of the certifying officer or the appellate authority referred to in section`
  line `32 to adjudicate upon the fairness or reasonableness of the provisions of any standing orders keeping in`
  line `view the provisions of the model standing orders referred to in section 29.`
  line
  line `(8) The certifying officer shall certify the draft standing orders or the modifications in the standing`
  line `orders referred to in sub-section (5), and shall within seven days thereafter send copies of the certified`
  line `standing orders or the modifications in the standing orders, authenticated in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed, to the employer and to the negotiating union or negotiating council or the Trade Union or`
  line `other representatives of the workers referred to in clause (ii) of sub-section (5).`
  line
  line `(9) The draft standing orders under sub-section (1) or draft of the modifications proposed in the`
  line `standing orders under sub-section (5) shall be accompanied by a statement giving such particulars, as`
  line `may be prescribed, of the workers employed in the industrial establishment, the Trade Union to which`
  line `they belong, and the negotiating union or negotiating council, if any.`
  line
  line `(10) Subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, a group of employers in similar establishments`
  line `may submit a joint draft of standing orders under this section and for the purposes of proceedings`
  line `specified in sub-sections (1), (5), (6), (8) and (9), the expressions "employer", "Trade Union" and`
  line `"negotiating union or negotiating council" shall respectively include all the employers, Trade Unions`
  line `and negotiating unions or negotiating council of such similar establishments, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(11) Without prejudice to the foregoing provisions of this section, the standing orders relating to an`
  line `industrial establishment or undertaking existing on the date of commencement of the relevant provisions`
  line `of this Code, shall, in so far as is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Code or rules made`
  line `thereunder, continue and be deemed to be the standing orders certified under sub-section (8) and`
  line `accordingly the provisions of this Chapter shall apply thereon.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (101458)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Certifying officers and appellate authority to have powers of civil court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101458&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every`
  line `certifying officer and the appellate authority referred to in section 32 shall have all the powers of a civil`
  line `court for the purposes of receiving evidence, administering oath, enforcing the attendance of witnesses,`
  line `and compelling the discovery and production of documents, and shall be deemed to be a civil court`
  line `within the meaning of sections 345 and 346 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(2) Clerical or arithmetical mistakes in any order passed by a certifying officer, or errors arising`
  line `therein from any accidental slip or omission may, at any time, be corrected by that officer or successor`
  line `in office of such officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (101459)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101459&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `An employer or Trade Union or the negotiating union or negotiating council, or`
  line `where there is no negotiating union or negotiating council in an industrial establishment or undertaking,`
  line `any union or such representative body of the workers of the industrial establishment or undertaking, if`
  line `not satisfied with the order of the certifying officer given under sub-section (5) of section 30, may file`
  line `an appeal within sixty days of receipt of the order of the certifying officer to the appellate authority`
  line `appointed by the appropriate Government, by notification, and such authority shall dispose of the appeal`
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (101460)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Date of operation of standing orders and its availability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101460&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The standing orders or`
  line `modified standing orders, as the case may be, shall, unless an appeal is preferred under section 32, come`
  line `into operation on the expiry of thirty days from the date on which authenticated copies thereof are sent`
  line `under sub-section (8) of section 30, or where an appeal as aforesaid is preferred, on the expiry of seven`
  line `days from the date on which copies of the order of the appellate authority are sent in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The text of a standing order as finally certified under this Code shall be maintained by the`
  line `employer in such language and in such manner for the information of the concerned workers as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (101461)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Register of standing orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101461&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `A copy of all standing orders as finally certified under this Code`
  line `shall be filed by the certifying officer in a register maintained for the purpose or uploaded in electronic`
  line `form or such other form as may be prescribed, and the certifying officer shall furnish a copy thereof to`
  line `any person applying therefor on payment of such fee as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (101462)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Duration and modification of standing orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101462&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The standing orders certified under subsection (8) of section 30 shall not, except on an agreement between the employer and the workers, or a`
  line `negotiating union or a Trade Union or other representative body of the workers, be liable to modification`
  line `until the expiry of six months from the date on which the standing orders or the last modifications`
  line `thereof came into operation.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1), an employer or worker or a Trade Union or other`
  line `representative body of the workers may apply to the certifying officer to have the standing orders`
  line `modified in such application as may be prescribed, which shall be accompanied by such copies of the`
  line `modifications proposed to be made, and where the modifications are proposed to be made by agreement`
  line `between the employer and the workers or a Trade Union or other representative body of the workers, a`
  line `certified copy of that agreement shall be filed alongwith the application.`
  line
  line `(3) The foregoing provisions of this Code shall apply in respect of an application under`
  line `sub-section (2) as they apply to the certification of the first time standing orders.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (101463)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Oral evidence in contradiction of standing orders not admissible.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101463&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `No oral evidence having`
  line `the effect of adding to or otherwise varying or contradicting standing order as finally certified under`
  line `this Chapter shall be admitted in any Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (101464)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Interpretation, etc., of standing orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101464&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `If any question arises as to the application, or`
  line `interpretation, of the standing orders certified under sub-section (8) of section 30 or the modification`
  line `made therein by an agreement entered into under sub-section (5) of that section, the employer or any`
  line `worker or workers concerned or the Trade Union in relation to the workers employed in the industrial`
  line `establishment or undertaking, wherein the question has arisen, may apply to the Tribunal, within the`
  line `local limits of whose territorial jurisdiction such establishment or the office, section or branch of the`
  line `undertaking is situated, to decide the question and such Tribunal shall, after giving all the parties`
  line `concerned a reasonable opportunity of being heard, decide the question and its decision shall be final`
  line `and binding on the concerned employer and the workers.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (102034)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Time limit for completing disciplinary proceedings and liability to pay subsistence allowance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=102034&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any worker is suspended by the employer pending investigation or inquiry into`
  line `complaints or charges of misconduct against him, such investigation or inquiry, or where there is an`
  line `investigation followed by an inquiry, both the investigation and inquiry shall be completed ordinarily`
  line `within a period of ninety days from the date of suspension.`
  line
  line `(2) The standing orders certified under sub-section (8) of section 30 or modified under section 35`
  line `shall provide that where a worker is suspended as referred to in sub-section (1), the employer in relation`
  line `to an industrial establishment or undertaking shall pay to such worker employed in such industrial`
  line `establishment or undertaking subsistence allowance at the rates specified in sub-section (3) for the`
  line `period during which such worker is placed under suspension pending investigation or inquiry into`
  line `complaints or charges of misconduct against such worker.`
  line
  line `(3) The amount of subsistence allowance payable under sub-section (2) shall be ---`
  line
  line `(a) at the rate of fifty per cent. of the wages which the worker was entitled to immediately`
  line `preceding the date of such suspension, for the first ninety days of suspension; and`
  line
  line `(b) at the rate of seventy-five per cent. of such wages for the remaining period of suspension,`
  line `if the delay in the completion of disciplinary proceedings against such worker is not directly`
  line `attributable to the conduct of such worker.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (101466)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101466&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government may, by notification, exempt, conditionally`
  line `or unconditionally, any industrial establishment or class of industrial establishments from all or any of`
  line `the provisions of this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (101467)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Notice of change.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101467&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `No employer, who proposes to effect any change in the conditions of service`
  line `applicable to any worker in respect of any matter specified in the Third Schedule, shall effect such`
  line change,---
  line
  line `(i) without giving to the workers likely to be affected by such change a notice in such manner`
  line `as may be prescribed of the nature of the change proposed to be effected; or`
  line
  line `(ii) within twenty-one days of giving such notice:`
  line
  line `Provided that no notice shall be required for effecting any such change---`
  line
  line `(a) where the change is effected in pursuance of any settlement or award;`
  line
  line `(b) where the workers likely to be affected by the change are persons to whom the`
  line `Fundamental and Supplementary Rules, Civil Services (Classification, Control and Appeal)`
  line `Rules, Civil Services (Temporary Service) Rules, Revised Leave Rules, Civil Services`
  line `Regulations, Civilians in Defence Services (Classification, Control and Appeal) Rules or the`
  line `Indian Railway Establishment Code or any other rules or regulations that may be notified in this`
  line `behalf by the appropriate Government in the Official Gazette, apply;`
  line
  line `(c) in case of emergent situation which requires change of shift or shift working, otherwise`
  line `than in accordance with standing orders, in consultation with Grievance Redressal Committee;`
  line
  line `(d) if such change is effected in accordance with the orders of the appropriate Government`
  line `or in pursuance of any settlement or award.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (101468)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Power of appropriate Government to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101468&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `Where the appropriate Government is of the`
  line `opinion that the application of the provisions of section 40 to any class of industrial establishments or`
  line `to any class of worker employed in any industrial establishment affect the employers in relation thereto`
  line `so prejudicially that such application may cause serious repercussion on the industry concerned and that`
  line `public interest so requires, the appropriate Government may, by notification, direct that the provisions`
  line `of the said section shall not apply or shall apply, subject to such conditions as may be specified in the`
  line `notification, to that class of industrial establishments or to that class of workers employed in any`
  line `industrial establishment.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (101469)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Voluntary reference of disputes to arbitration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101469&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any industrial dispute exists or is`
  line `apprehended and the employer and the workers agree to refer the dispute to arbitration, they may, by a`
  line `written agreement, refer the dispute to arbitration, and the reference shall be to such person or persons`
  line `as an arbitrator or arbitrators as may be specified in the arbitration agreement.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an arbitration agreement provides for a reference of the dispute to an even number of`
  line `arbitrators, the agreement shall provide for the appointment of another person as umpire who shall enter`
  line `upon the reference, if the arbitrators are equally divided in their opinion, and the award of the umpire`
  line `shall prevail and shall be deemed to be the arbitration award for the purposes of this Code.`
  line
  line `(3) An arbitration agreement referred to in sub-section (1) shall be in such form and shall be signed`
  line `by the parties thereto in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) A copy of the arbitration agreement shall be forwarded to the appropriate Government and the`
  line `conciliation officer.`
  line
  line `(5) Where an industrial dispute has been referred to arbitration and the appropriate Government is`
  line `satisfied that the persons making the reference represent the majority of each party, the appropriate`
  line `Government may issue a notification in such manner as may be prescribed; and when any such`
  line `notification is issued, the employers and workers who are not parties to the arbitration agreement but`
  line `are concerned in the dispute, shall be given an opportunity of presenting their case before the arbitrator`
  line `or arbitrators:`
  line
  line `Provided that---`
  line
  line `(i) where such industrial dispute is the industrial dispute other than the termination of individual`
  line `worker by way of discharge, dismissal, retrenchment or otherwise, the workers shall be represented`
  line `before the arbitrator,---`
  line
  line `(a) where there is negotiating union or negotiating council, by the negotiating union or`
  line `negotiating council, as the case may be; or`
  line
  line `(b) where there is no negotiating union or negotiating council, by the Trade Union; or`
  line
  line `(c) where there is no Trade Union, by such representatives of the workers chosen in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(ii) where such industrial dispute relates to termination of individual worker by way of discharge,`
  line `dismissal, retrenchment or otherwise, the concerned workers shall be represented in person or`
  line `through a representative authorised by him.`
  line
  line `(6) The arbitrator or arbitrators shall investigate the dispute and submit to the appropriate`
  line `Government the arbitration award signed by the arbitrator or all the arbitrators, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(7) Where an industrial dispute has been referred to arbitration and a notification has been issued`
  line `under sub-section (5), the appropriate Government may, by order, prohibit the continuance of any strike`
  line `or lock-out in connection with such dispute which may be in existence on the date of the reference.`
  line
  line `(8) Nothing in the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996, shall apply to arbitrations under this`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (101470)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Conciliation officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101470&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may, by notification, appoint such`
  line `number of persons, as it thinks fit to be conciliation officers, charged with the duty of mediating in and`
  line `promoting the settlement of industrial disputes.`
  line
  line `(2) A conciliation officer may be appointed for a specified area or for specified industries in a`
  line `specified area or for one or more specified industries and either permanently or for a limited period.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (101471)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Industrial Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101471&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may, by notification, constitute one or`
  line `more Industrial Tribunals for the adjudication of industrial disputes and for performing such other`
  line `functions as may be assigned to them under this Code and the Tribunal so constituted by the Central`
  line `Government shall also exercise the jurisdiction, powers and authority conferred on the Tribunal, as`
  line `defined in clause (m) of section 2 of the Employees' Provident Funds and Miscellaneous Provisions`
  line `Act, 1952 (19 of 1952) by or under that Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Industrial Tribunal shall consist of two members to be appointed by the appropriate`
  line `Government out of whom one shall be a Judicial Member and the other, an Administrative Member.`
  line
  line `(3) A bench of the Tribunal shall consist of a Judicial Member and an Administrative Member or`
  line `single Judicial Member or single Administrative Member.`
  line
  line `(4) The qualifications for appointment, method of recruitment, term of office, salaries and`
  line `allowances, resignation, removal and the other terms of conditions of service of the Judicial Member`
  line `and the Administrative Member of the Tribunal constituted by the Central Government shall be in`
  line `accordance with the rules made under section 184 of the Finance Act, 2017 (7 of 2017):`
  line
  line `Provided that a person who has held a post below the rank of Joint Secretary to the Government of`
  line `India or an equivalent rank in the Central Government or a State Government, shall not be eligible to`
  line `be appointed as an Administrative Member of the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(5) The term of office of the Judicial Member and the Administrative Member of a Tribunal`
  line `constituted by the State Government under sub-section (1), their salaries and allowances, resignation,`
  line `removal and other terms and conditions of service shall be such as may be prescribed by the State`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(6) The salary and allowances and the terms and conditions of service of the Judicial Member or`
  line `Administrative Member referred to in sub-section (2) and appointed by a State Government shall not`
  line `be varied to his disadvantage after his appointment.`
  line
  line `(7) The procedure of the Tribunal (including distribution of cases in the benches of the Tribunal)`
  line `shall be such as may be prescribed, provided a bench consisting of a Judicial Member and an`
  line `Administrative Member shall entertain and decide the cases only relating to---`
  line
  line `(a) the application and interpretation of standing order;`
  line
  line `(b) discharge or dismissal of workmen including reinstatement of, or grant of relief to, workmen`
  line dismissed;
  line
  line `(c) illegality or otherwise of a strike or lockout;`
  line
  line `(d) retrenchment of workmen and closure of establishment; and`
  line
  line `(e) Trade Union disputes,`
  line
  line `and the remaining cases shall be entertained and decided by the bench of the Tribunal consisting either`
  line `a Judicial Member or an Administrative Member of the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(8) The Judicial Member shall preside over the Tribunal where the bench of the Tribunal consists of`
  line `one Judicial Member and one Administrative Member.`
  line
  line `(9) If, for any reason, a vacancy (other than a temporary absence) occurs in a National Industrial`
  line `Tribunal or a Tribunal, then, such vacancy shall be filled up in such manner as may be prescribed,`
  line `without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (4) or sub-section (5), as the case may be, and the`
  line `proceeding shall be continued before such National Industrial Tribunal or Tribunal, as the case may be,`
  line `from the stage at which the vacancy is filled.`
  line
  line `(10) The appropriate Government may provide such number of officers and other staff as it thinks`
  line `fit in consultation with the Judicial Member of the Tribunal which may be required for the due discharge`
  line `of the functioning of the Tribunal.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (101472)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Finality of constitution of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101472&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `No notification of the appropriate Government`
  line `appointing any person as a Judicial Member or an Administrative Member of a Tribunal shall be called`
  line `in question in any manner; and no act or proceeding before the Tribunal shall be called in question in`
  line `any manner on the ground mainly of the existence of any vacancy in, or defect in the constitution of`
  line `such Tribunal.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (101473)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `National Industrial Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101473&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, constitute`
  line `one or more National Industrial Tribunals for the adjudication of industrial disputes which, in the`
  line `opinion of the Central Government, involve questions of national importance or are of such a nature`
  line `that industrial establishments situated in more than one State are likely to be interested in, or affected`
  line `by, such disputes.`
  line
  line `(2) A National Industrial Tribunal shall consist of two members to be appointed by the Central`
  line `Government out of whom one shall be a Judicial Member and the other, an Administrative Member.`
  line
  line `(3) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as the Judicial Member of a National Industrial`
  line `Tribunal unless he is, or has been, a Judge of a High Court.`
  line
  line `(4) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as Administrative Member of a National`
  line `Industrial Tribunal unless, he is or has been Secretary to the Government of India or holding an`
  line `equivalent rank in the Central Government or State Government, having adequate experience of`
  line `handling the labour related matters.`
  line
  line `(5) The Judicial Member shall preside over a National Industrial Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(6) The procedure of selection of Judicial Member and Administrative Member of the National`
  line `Industrial Tribunal, their salaries, allowances and other terms and conditions of service shall be such as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(7) The Central Government may provide such number of officers and other staff as it thinks fit in`
  line `consultation with the Judicial Member of the National Industrial Tribunal which may be required for`
  line `the due discharge of the functioning of the National Industrial Tribunal.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (101474)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Decision of Tribunal or National Industrial Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101474&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) The decision of a Tribunal or a`
  line `National Industrial Tribunal, as the case may be, shall be by consensus of the members.`
  line
  line `(2) If the members of a Tribunal or a National Industrial Tribunal differ in opinion on any point,`
  line `they shall state the point or points on which they differ, and make a reference to the appropriate`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) The appropriate Government shall, on receipt of a reference made under sub-section (2), appoint`
  line `a Judicial Member of other Tribunal or a National Industrial Tribunal, who shall hear the point or points`
  line `himself and such point or points shall be decided according to the majority of the members of a Tribunal`
  line `or a National Industrial Tribunal, as the case may be, who have first heard the case, including the`
  line `Judicial Member of the other Tribunal who heard the case thereafter.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (101475)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Disqualifications for members of Tribunal and National Industrial Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101475&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `No person`
  line `shall be appointed to, or continue in, the office of the member of a Tribunal or National Industrial`
  line `Tribunal, respectively, if---`
  line
  line `(a) he is not an independent person; or`
  line
  line `(b) he has attained the age of sixty-five years.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this section "independent person" means a person who is`
  line `unconnected with the industrial dispute referred to a Tribunal or National Industrial Tribunal or with`
  line `any industry directly affected by such dispute.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (102035)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Procedure and powers of arbitrator, conciliation officer, Tribunal and National Industrial Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=102035&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Code and the rules that may be made in this behalf, an`
  line `arbitrator, conciliation officer, Tribunal or National Industrial Tribunal shall follow such procedure as`
  line `the arbitrator, conciliation officer, Tribunal or National Industrial Tribunal may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(2) A conciliation officer or an officer authorised in this behalf by the Tribunal or National Industrial`
  line `Tribunal may, for the purpose of inquiry into any existing or apprehended industrial dispute, after giving`
  line `reasonable notice, enter the premises occupied by any establishment to which the dispute relates.`
  line
  line `(3) The conciliation officer, Tribunal and National Industrial Tribunal shall have the same powers`
  line `as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure,1908 (5 of 1908), when trying a suit, in`
  line `respect of the following matters, namely: ---`
  line
  line `(a) enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) compelling the production of documents and material objects;`
  line
  line `(c) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses;`
  line
  line `(d) in respect of such other matters as may be prescribed,`
  line
  line `and every inquiry or investigation by Tribunal or National Industrial Tribunal, shall be deemed to be a`
  line `judicial proceeding within the meaning of sections 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(4) A conciliation officer may enforce the attendance of any person for the purpose of examination`
  line `of such person or call for and inspect any document which he has ground for considering to be relevant`
  line `to the industrial dispute or to be necessary for the purpose of verifying the implementation of any award`
  line `or carrying out any other duty imposed on him under this Code, and for the aforesaid purposes, the`
  line `conciliation officer shall have the same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him`
  line `or of compelling the production of documents.`
  line
  line `(5) The appropriate Government may, if it so thinks fit, appoint one or more persons having special`
  line `knowledge of the matter under consideration as assessors or experts to advise a Tribunal or National`
  line `Industrial Tribunal, as the case may be, in respect of any proceeding before either of the said Tribunals.`
  line
  line `(6) All conciliation officers and the members of a Tribunal or National Industrial Tribunal shall be`
  line `deemed to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(7) Subject to any rules made under this Code, the costs of, and incidental to, any proceeding before`
  line `a Tribunal or National Industrial Tribunal shall be in the discretion of that Tribunal or National`
  line `Industrial Tribunal and the Tribunal or National Industrial Tribunal, as the case may be, shall have full`
  line `powers to determine by and to whom and to what extent and subject to what conditions, if any, such`
  line `costs are to be paid, and to give all necessary directions for the purposes aforesaid and such costs may,`
  line `on application made to the appropriate Government by the person entitled, be recovered by that`
  line `Government in the same manner as an arrear of land revenue.`
  line
  line `(8) Every Tribunal or National Industrial Tribunal shall be deemed to be civil court for the purposes`
  line `of sections 345, 346, and 348 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(9) Every award made, order issued or settlement arrived at by or before a Tribunal or a National`
  line `Industrial Tribunal shall be executed in accordance with the procedure laid down for execution of orders`
  line `and decree of a civil court under Order XXI of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) and for`
  line `that purpose such Tribunal or National Industrial Tribunal shall be deemed to be a civil court.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (102036)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Powers of Tribunal and National Industrial Tribunal to give appropriate relief in case of discharge or dismissal of worker.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=102036&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the application under sub-section (6) of section 53`
  line `relating to an industrial dispute involving discharge or dismissal or otherwise termination of a worker`
  line `has been made to a Tribunal or has been referred to a National Industrial Tribunal for adjudication, and,`
  line `in the course of adjudication proceedings, the Tribunal or National Industrial Tribunal, as the case may`
  line `be, is satisfied that the order of discharge or dismissal or otherwise termination was not justified, it may,`
  line `by its award, set aside the order of discharge or dismissal or termination and direct reinstatement of the`
  line `worker on such terms and conditions, if any, as it thinks fit, or give such other relief to the worker`
  line `including the award of any lesser punishment in lieu of discharge or dismissal or otherwise termination,`
  line `as the circumstances of the case may require.`
  line
  line `(2) A Tribunal or National Industrial Tribunal, as the case may be, may, in the interest of justice,`
  line `grant such interim relief to the worker referred to in sub-section (1) during the pendency of the industrial`
  line `dispute as the circumstances of the case may require: Provided that in any proceeding under this subsection the Tribunal or National Industrial Tribunal, as the case may be, shall rely only on the materials`
  line `on record and shall not take any fresh evidence in relation to the matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (101478)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Transfer of pending cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101478&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the date of commencement of this Code, the cases`
  line `pending immediately before such commencement---`
  line
  line `(a) in the Labour Court and the Tribunal constituted under the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14`
  line `of 1947), shall be transferred to the Tribunal having corresponding jurisdiction under this Code;`
  line
  line `(b) in the National Tribunal constituted under the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947) shall`
  line `be transferred to the National Industrial Tribunal having corresponding jurisdiction under this Code.`
  line
  line `(2) The cases transferred under sub-section (1) to the Tribunal or the National Industrial Tribunal`
  line `shall be dealt with de novo or from the stage at which they were pending before such transfer, as it`
  line `may deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (101479)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Adjustment of services of presiding officers under repealed Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101479&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `A presiding officer of a`
  line `Labour Court or Tribunal or, as the case may be, National Tribunal, constituted under the Industrial`
  line `Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), holding office as such immediately before the commencement of this`
  line `Code and is qualified to be appointed under this Code, shall be the Judicial Member of the Tribunal or,`
  line `as the case may be, the Judicial Member of the National Industrial Tribunal, and shall continue as such`
  line `for the remaining period of his office.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (101480)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Conciliation and adjudication of dispute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101480&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any industrial dispute exists or is`
  line `apprehended or a notice under section 62 has been given, the conciliation officer shall, hold conciliation`
  line `proceedings in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the conciliation officer shall not hold any such proceedings relating to the industrial`
  line `dispute after two years from the date on which such industrial dispute arose.`
  line
  line `(2) The conciliation officer shall, for the purpose of bringing about a settlement of the dispute,`
  line `without delay, investigate the dispute and all matters affecting the merits and right settlement thereof`
  line `and may do all such things as he thinks fit for the purpose of inducing the parties to come to a fair and`
  line `amicable settlement of the dispute.`
  line
  line `(3) If a settlement of the dispute or of any of the matters in dispute is arrived at in the course of the`
  line `conciliation proceedings, the conciliation officer shall send a report thereof to the appropriate`
  line `Government or an officer authorised in this behalf by the appropriate Government together with a`
  line `memorandum of the settlement signed by the parties to the dispute.`
  line
  line `(4) If no such settlement is arrived at, the conciliation officer shall, as soon as practicable, after the`
  line `close of the investigation, send to the concerned parties and to the appropriate Government a full report,`
  line `in the electronic or other form as may be prescribed, setting forth the steps taken by him for ascertaining`
  line `the facts and circumstances relating to the dispute and for bringing about a settlement thereof, together`
  line `with a full statement of such facts and circumstances, and the reasons on account of which, in his`
  line `opinion, a settlement could not be arrived at.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (4), the conciliation officer shall send the`
  line `report to the concerned parties and the appropriate Government within forty-five days of the`
  line `commencement of the conciliation proceedings or within such shorter period as may be fixed by the`
  line `appropriate Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a conciliation officer receives notice under section 62, he shall send the report`
  line `to the concerned parties and to the appropriate Government within fourteen days of the commencement`
  line `of the conciliation proceedings:`
  line
  line `Provided further that subject to the approval of the conciliation officer, the time may be extended by`
  line `such period as may be agreed upon in writing by the concerned parties to the dispute.`
  line
  line `(6) Any concerned party may make application in the prescribed form to the Tribunal in the matters`
  line `not settled by the conciliation officer under this section within ninety days from the date on which the`
  line `report under sub-section (4) is received to the concerned party and the Tribunal shall decide such`
  line `application in the prescribed manner.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (101481)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Reference to and functions of National Industrial Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101481&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `may refer an industrial dispute to a National Industrial Tribunal which in the opinion of such`
  line `Government involves question of national importance or is of such a nature that industrial`
  line `establishments situated in more than one State are likely to be interested in, or affected by such industrial`
  line dispute.
  line
  line `(2) Where an industrial dispute has been referred under sub-section (1) or transferred under section`
  line `92 by the Central Government to a National Industrial Tribunal for adjudication, it shall hold its`
  line `proceedings expeditiously and shall, within the period specified in the order referring or transferring`
  line `such industrial dispute or further period extended by the Central Government, submit its award to that`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (101482)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Form of award, its communication and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101482&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) The award of---`
  line
  line `(i) a Tribunal delivered by a bench consisting of a Judicial Member and an Administrative`
  line `Member or a single Judicial Member or a single Administrative Member; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a National Industrial Tribunal,`
  line
  line `shall be in writing and shall be signed electronically or otherwise, as the case may be, by both the`
  line `Judicial Member and the Administrative Member or either by the Judicial Member or the`
  line `Administrative Member by whom the award is delivered.`
  line
  line `(2) Every arbitration award and every award of Tribunal or National Industrial Tribunal shall be`
  line `communicated to the parties concerned and the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(3) An award made under this Code shall become enforceable on the expiry of thirty days from the`
  line `date of its communication under sub-section (2):`
  line
  line `Provided that---`
  line
  line `(a) if the appropriate Government is of the opinion in any case, where the award has been given`
  line `by a Tribunal in relation to an industrial dispute to which it is a party; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the Central Government is of opinion in any case, where the award has been given by a`
  line `National Industrial Tribunal,`
  line
  line `that it will be inexpedient on public grounds affecting national economy or social justice to give effect`
  line `to the whole or any part of the award, the appropriate Government, or as the case may be, the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, declare that the award shall not become enforceable on the expiry of`
  line `the said period of thirty days.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any declaration has been made in relation to an award under the proviso to`
  line `sub-section (3), the appropriate Government or the Central Government, as the case may be, may, within`
  line `ninety days from the date of communication of the award under sub-section (2), make an order rejecting`
  line `or modifying the award, and shall, on the first available opportunity, lay the award together with a copy`
  line `of the order before the Legislature of the State, if the order has been made by a State Government, or`
  line `before Parliament, if the order has been made by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) Where any award as rejected or modified by an order made under sub-section (4) is laid before`
  line `the Legislature of a State or before Parliament, such award shall become enforceable on the expiry of`
  line `fifteen days from the date on which it is so laid; and where no order under sub-section (4) is made in`
  line `pursuance of a declaration under the proviso to sub-section (3), the award shall become enforceable on`
  line `the expiry of the period of ninety days referred to in sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(6) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (3) and sub-section (5) regarding the enforceability of`
  line `an award, the award shall come into operation with effect from such date as may be specified therein,`
  line `but where no date is so specified, it shall come into operation on the date when the award becomes`
  line `enforceable under sub-section (3) or sub-section (5), as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (101483)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Payment of full wages to worker pending proceedings in higher Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101483&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `Where in any case,`
  line `a Tribunal or a National Industrial Tribunal by its award directs reinstatement of any worker and the`
  line `employer prefers any proceedings against such award in a High Court or the Supreme Court, the`
  line `employer shall be liable to pay such worker, during the period of pendency of such proceedings in the`
  line `High Court or the Supreme Court, full wages last drawn by him, inclusive of any maintenance allowance`
  line `admissible to him under any rule if the worker had not been employed in any establishment during such`
  line `period and an affidavit by such worker had been filed to that effect in such Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that where it is proved to the satisfaction of the High Court or the Supreme Court that such`
  line `worker had been employed and had been receiving adequate remuneration during any such period or`
  line `part thereof, the Court shall order that no wages shall be payable under this section for such period or`
  line `part, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (101484)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Persons on whom settlements and awards are binding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101484&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) A settlement arrived at by`
  line `agreement between the employer and worker otherwise than in the course of conciliation proceeding`
  line `shall be binding on the parties to the agreement.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (3), an arbitration award which has become enforceable`
  line `shall be binding on the parties to the agreement who referred the dispute to arbitration.`
  line
  line `(3) A settlement arrived at in the course of conciliation proceedings under this Code or an arbitration`
  line `or an award of a Tribunal or National Industrial Tribunal which has become enforceable shall be binding`
  line on---
  line
  line `(a) all parties to the industrial dispute;`
  line
  line `(b) all other parties summoned to appear in the proceedings as parties to the dispute, unless the`
  line `arbitrator, Tribunal or National Industrial Tribunal, as the case may be, records the opinion that they`
  line `were so summoned without proper cause;`
  line
  line `(c) where a party referred to in clause (a) or clause (b) is an employer, his heirs, successors or`
  line `assigns in respect of the establishment to which the dispute relates;`
  line
  line `(d) where a party referred to in clause (a) or clause (b) is composed of workers, all persons who`
  line `were employed in the establishment or part of the establishment, as the case may be, to which the`
  line `dispute relates on the date of the dispute and all persons who subsequently become employed in that`
  line `establishment or part.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (101485)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Period of operation of settlements and awards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101485&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) A settlement shall come into operation`
  line `on such date as is agreed upon by the parties to the dispute, and if no date is agreed upon, on the date`
  line `on which the memorandum of the settlement is signed by the parties to the dispute.`
  line
  line `(2) Such settlement shall be binding for such period as is agreed upon by the parties, and if no such`
  line `period is agreed upon, for a period of six months from the date on which the memorandum of settlement`
  line `is signed by the parties to the dispute, and shall continue to be binding on the parties after the expiry of`
  line `the period aforesaid, until the expiry of sixty days from the date on which a notice in writing of an`
  line `intention to terminate the settlement is given by one of the parties to the other party or parties to the`
  line settlement.
  line
  line `(3) An award shall, subject to the provisions of this section, remain in operation for a period of one`
  line `year from the date on which the award becomes enforceable under section 55:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appropriate Government may reduce the said period and fix such period as it thinks`
  line `fit:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the appropriate Government may, before expiry of the said period, extend the`
  line `period of operation by any period not exceeding one year at a time as it thinks fit so, however, that the`
  line `total period of operation of any award does not exceed three years from the date on which it came into`
  line operation.
  line
  line `(4) Where the appropriate Government, whether of its own motion or on the application of any party`
  line `bound by the award, considers that since the award was made, there has been a material change in the`
  line `circumstances on which it was based, the appropriate Government may refer the award or part of it to`
  line `the Tribunal, if the award is made by the Tribunal for decision whether the period of operation should`
  line `not, by reason of such change, be shortened and the decision of the Tribunal on such reference shall be`
  line final.
  line
  line `(5) Nothing contained in sub-section (3) shall apply to any award which by its nature, terms or other`
  line `circumstances does not impose, after it has been given effect to, any continuing obligation on the parties`
  line `bound by the award.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding the expiry of the period of operation under sub-section (3), the award shall`
  line `continue to be binding on the parties until a period of sixty days has elapsed from the date on which`
  line `notice is given by any party bound by the award to the other party or parties intimating its intention to`
  line `terminate the award.`
  line
  line `(7) No notice given under sub-section (2) or sub-section (6) shall have effect, unless it is given by a`
  line `party representing the majority of persons bound by the settlement or award, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (101486)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Recovery of money due from employer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101486&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any money is due to a worker from an`
  line `employer under a settlement or an award or under the provisions of Chapter IX or Chapter X, the worker`
  line `himself or any other person authorised by him in writing in this behalf, or, in the case of the death of`
  line `the worker, his assignee or heirs may, without prejudice to any other mode of recovery, make an`
  line `application to the appropriate Government for the recovery of the money due to him, and if the`
  line `appropriate Government is satisfied that any money is so due, it shall issue a certificate for that amount`
  line `to the Collector who shall proceed to recover the same in the same manner as an arrear of land revenue:`
  line
  line `Provided that every such application shall be made within one year from the date on which the`
  line `money became due to the worker from the employer:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any such application may be entertained after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `one year, if the appropriate Government is satisfied that the applicant had sufficient cause for not`
  line `making the application within the said period.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any worker is entitled to receive from the employer any money or any benefit which is`
  line `capable of being computed in terms of money and if any question arises as to the amount of money due`
  line `or as to the amount at which such benefit should be computed, then the question may, subject to any`
  line `rules that may be made under this Code, be decided by such Tribunal as may be specified in this behalf`
  line `by the appropriate Government within a period not exceeding three months:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Tribunal considers it necessary or expedient so to do, it may, for reasons to`
  line `be recorded in writing, extend such period by such further period as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of computing the money value of a benefit referred to in sub-section (2), the`
  line `Tribunal may, if it so thinks fit, appoint a Commissioner who shall, after taking such evidence as may`
  line `be necessary, submit a report to the Tribunal and the Tribunal shall determine the amount after`
  line `considering the report of the Commissioner and other circumstances of the case.`
  line
  line `(4) The decision of the Tribunal shall be forwarded by it to the appropriate Government and any`
  line `amount found due by the Tribunal may be recovered in the manner provided for in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(5) Where workers employed under the same employer are entitled to receive from him any money`
  line `or any benefit capable of being computed in terms of money, then, subject to such rules as may be made`
  line `in this behalf, a single application for the recovery of the amount due may be made on behalf of or in`
  line `respect of any number of such workers.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (101487)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Commencement and conclusion of proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101487&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) A conciliation proceeding shall be`
  line `deemed to have commenced on the date on which the first meeting is held by the conciliation officer in`
  line `an industrial dispute after the receipt of the notice of strike or lock-out by the conciliation officer.`
  line
  line `(2) A conciliation proceeding shall be deemed to have concluded---`
  line
  line `(a) where a settlement is arrived at, when a memorandum of the settlement is signed by the`
  line `parties to the dispute;`
  line
  line `(b) where no settlement is arrived at, and failure of conciliation is recorded by the conciliation`
  line `officer; or (c) when a reference is made to a National Industrial Tribunal, under this Code, during`
  line `the pendency of conciliation proceedings.`
  line
  line `(3) Proceedings before an arbitrator or a Tribunal or a National Industrial Tribunal under this Code`
  line `shall be deemed to have commenced on the date of filing application or appeal or on the date of`
  line `reference of the dispute for arbitration or adjudication, as the case may be, and such proceedings shall`
  line `be deemed to have concluded on the date on which the award becomes enforceable.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (101488)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Certain matters to be kept confidential.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101488&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `There shall not be included in any report or award`
  line `under this Code, any information obtained by a conciliation officer, arbitrator, Tribunal or National`
  line `Industrial Tribunal, in the course of any investigation or inquiry as to a Trade Union or as to any`
  line `individual business (whether carried on by a person, firm or company) which is not available otherwise`
  line `than through the evidence given before such conciliation officer, arbitrator, Tribunal, or National`
  line `Industrial Tribunal, if the Trade Union, person, firm or company, in question has made a request in`
  line `writing to the conciliation officer, arbitrator, Tribunal or National Industrial Tribunal, as the case may`
  line `be, that such information shall be treated as confidential; nor shall such conciliation officer, or the`
  line `arbitrator, or the presiding officer of a Tribunal or a National Industrial Tribunal or any person present`
  line `at or concerned in the proceedings disclose any such information without the consent in writing of the`
  line `secretary of the Trade Union or the person, firm or company in question, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall apply to a disclosure of any such information`
  line `for the purposes of a prosecution under section 193 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (101489)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Prohibition of strikes and lock-outs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101489&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person employed in an industrial establishment`
  line `shall go on strike, in breach of contract---`
  line
  line `(a) without giving to the employer notice of strike, as hereinafter provided, within sixty days`
  line `before striking; or`
  line
  line `(b) within fourteen days of giving such notice; or`
  line
  line `(c) before the expiry of the date of strike specified in any such notice; or`
  line
  line `(d) during the pendency of any conciliation proceedings before a conciliation officer and seven`
  line `days after the conclusion of such proceedings; or`
  line
  line `(e) during the pendency of proceedings before a Tribunal or a National Industrial Tribunal and`
  line `sixty days, after the conclusion of such proceedings; or`
  line
  line `(f) during the pendency of arbitration proceedings before an arbitrator and sixty days after the`
  line `conclusion of such proceedings, where a notification has been issued under sub-section (5) of section`
  line `42; or`
  line
  line `(g) during any period in which a settlement or award is in operation, in respect of any of the matters`
  line `covered by the settlement or award.`
  line
  line `(2) No employer of an industrial establishment shall lock-out any of his workers---`
  line
  line `(a) without giving them notice of lock-out as hereinafter provided, within sixty days before`
  line `locking-out; or`
  line
  line `(b) within fourteen days of giving such notice; or`
  line
  line `(c) before the expiry of the date of lock-out specified in any such notice as aforesaid; or`
  line
  line `(d) during the pendency of any conciliation proceedings before a conciliation officer and seven`
  line `days after the conclusion of such proceedings; or`
  line
  line `(e) during the pendency of proceedings before a Tribunal or a National Industrial Tribunal and`
  line `sixty days, after the conclusion of such proceedings; or`
  line
  line `(f) during the pendency of arbitration proceedings before an arbitrator and sixty days after the`
  line `conclusion of such proceedings, where a notification has been issued under sub-section (5) of section`
  line `42; or`
  line
  line `(g) during any period in which a settlement or award is in operation, in respect of any of the`
  line `matters covered by the settlement or award.`
  line
  line `(3) The notice of strike or lock-out under this section shall not be necessary where there is already`
  line `in existence a strike or, as the case may be, lock-out, but the employer shall send intimation of such`
  line `lock-out or strike on the day on which it is declared, to such authority as may be specified by the`
  line `appropriate Government either generally or for a particular area or for a particular class of services.`
  line
  line `(4) The notice of strike referred to in sub-section (1) shall be given by such number of persons to`
  line `such person or persons and in such manner, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The notice of lock-out referred to in sub-section (2) shall be given in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(6) If on any day an employer receives from any person employed by him any such notices as are`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1) or gives to any person employed by him any such notices as are referred`
  line `to in sub-section (2), he shall within five days thereof report to the appropriate Government or to such`
  line `authority as that Government may prescribe and to the conciliation officer, the number of such notices`
  line `received or given on that day.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (101490)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Illegal strikes and lock-outs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101490&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1) A strike or lock-out shall be illegal, if it is---`
  line
  line `(i) commenced or declared in contravention of section 62; or`
  line
  line `(ii) continued in contravention of an order made under sub-section (7) of section 42.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a strike or lock-out in pursuance of an industrial dispute has already commenced and is`
  line `in existence at the time of the filing of the application relating to such industrial dispute in the Tribunal`
  line `or of the reference of such industrial dispute to an arbitrator or a National Industrial Tribunal, the`
  line `continuance of such strike or lock-out shall not be deemed to be illegal, provided that such strike or`
  line `lock-out was not at its commencement in contravention of the provisions of this Code or the continuance`
  line `thereof was not prohibited under sub-section (7) of section 42.`
  line
  line `(3) A lock-out declared in consequence of an illegal strike or a strike declared in consequence of an`
  line `illegal lock-out shall not be deemed to be illegal.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (101491)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Prohibition of financial aid to illegal strikes or lock-outs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101491&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `No person shall knowingly spend`
  line `or apply any money in direct furtherance or support of any illegal strike or lock-out.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (101492)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Application of sections 67 to 69.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101492&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) Sections 67 to 69 (both inclusive) shall not apply to`
  line `industrial establishments to which Chapter X applies; or`
  line
  line `(a) to industrial establishments in which less than fifty workers on an average per working day`
  line `have been employed in the preceding calendar month; or`
  line
  line `(b) to industrial establishments which are of a seasonal character or in which work is performed`
  line intermittently.
  line
  line `(2) If a question arises whether an industrial establishment is of a seasonal character or whether work`
  line `is performed therein only intermittently, the decision of the appropriate Government thereon shall be`
  line final.
  line
  line `Explanation.--- In this section and in sections 67, 68 and 69, industrial establishment shall mean a---`
  line
  line `(i) factory as defined in clause (m) of section 2 of the Factories Act, 1948 (63 of 1948); or`
  line
  line `(ii) mine as defined in clause (j) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Mines Act, 1952 (35 of`
  line `1952); or`
  line
  line `(iii) plantation as defined in clause (f) of section 2 of the Plantations Labour Act, 1951 (69 of`
  line `1951).`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (101493)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Definition of continuous service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101493&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `In this Chapter, continuous service in relation to a worker,`
  line `means the uninterrupted service of such worker, including his service which may be interrupted on`
  line `account of sickness or authorised leave or an accident or a strike which is not illegal or a lock-out or a`
  line `cessation of work which is not due to any fault on the part of the worker.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--- For the purposes of this section, where a worker is not in continuous service for a`
  line `period of one year or six months, he shall be deemed to be in continuous service under an employer---`
  line
  line `(a) for a period of one year, if the worker during a period of twelve months preceding the date`
  line `with reference to which calculation is to be made has actually worked under the employer for not`
  line `less than---`
  line
  line `(i) one hundred and ninety days in the case of a worker employed below ground in a mine;`
  line and
  line
  line `(ii) two hundred and forty days, in any other case;`
  line
  line `(b) for a period of six months, if the worker during a period of six months preceding the date with`
  line `reference to which calculation is to be made has actually worked under the employer for not less`
  line than---
  line
  line `(i) ninety-five days in the case of worker employed below ground in a mine; and`
  line
  line `(ii) one`
  line `hundred and twenty days, in any other case.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--- For the purposes of Explanation 1, the number of days on which a worker has`
  line `actually worked under an employer shall include the days on which---`
  line
  line `(i) he has been laid-off under an agreement or as permitted by or under this Code or any other`
  line `law applicable to the industrial establishment for the time being in force; or`
  line
  line `(ii) he has been on leave on full wages earned in the previous years; or`
  line
  line `(iii) he has been absent due to temporary disablement caused by accident arising out of and in`
  line `the course of his employment; or`
  line
  line `(iv) in the case of a female, she has been on maternity leave, so however, that the total period`
  line `of such maternity leave does not exceed the period as specified in the Maternity Benefit Act,`
  line `1961 (53 of 1961).`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (101494)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Rights of workers laid-off for compensation, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101494&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `Whenever a worker (other than a badli`
  line `worker or a casual worker) whose name is borne on the muster rolls of an industrial establishment and`
  line `who has completed not less than one year of continuous service under an employer is laid-off, whether`
  line `continuously or intermittently, he shall be paid by the employer for all days during which he is so laidoff, except for such weekly holidays as may intervene, compensation which shall be equal to fifty per`
  line `cent. of the total of the basic wages and dearness allowance that would have been payable to him, had`
  line `he not been so laid-off:`
  line
  line `Provided that if during any period of twelve months, a worker is so laid-off for more than forty-five`
  line `days, no such compensation shall be payable in respect of any period of the lay-off after the expiry of`
  line `the first forty-five days, if there is an agreement to that effect between the worker and the employer:`
  line
  line `Provided further that it shall be lawful for the employer in any case falling within the foregoing`
  line `proviso to retrench the worker in accordance with the provisions contained in section 70 at any time`
  line `after the expiry of the first forty-five days of the lay-off and when he does so, any compensation paid`
  line `to the worker for having been laid-off during the preceding twelve months may be set off against the`
  line `compensation payable for retrenchment.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this section "badli worker" means a worker who is employed in`
  line `an industrial establishment in the place of another worker whose name is borne on the muster rolls of`
  line `the establishment, but shall cease to be regarded as such, if he has completed one year of continuous`
  line `service in the establishment.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (101495)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Duty of an employer to maintain muster rolls of workers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101495&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding that workers in`
  line `any industrial establishment have been laid-off. it shall be the duty of every employer to maintain for`
  line `the purposes of this Chapter a muster roll, and to provide for the making of entries therein by workers`
  line `who may present themselves for work at the establishment at the appointed time during normal working`
  line hours.
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (101496)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Workers not entitled for compensation in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101496&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `No compensation shall be paid to`
  line `a worker who has been laid-off---`
  line
  line `(i) if he refuses to accept any alternative employment in the same establishment from which he`
  line `has been laid-off, or in any other establishment belonging to the same employer situate in the same`
  line `town or village or situate within a radius of eight kilometres from the establishment to which he`
  line `belongs, if, in the opinion of the employer, such alternative employment does not call for any special`
  line `skill or previous experience and can be done by the worker, provided that the wages which would`
  line `normally have been paid to the worker are offered for the alternative employment also;`
  line
  line `(ii) if he does not present himself for work at the establishment at the appointed time during`
  line `normal working hours at least once a day;`
  line
  line `(iii) if such laying-off is due to a strike or slowing-down of production on the part of workers in`
  line `another part of the establishment.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (101497)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Conditions precedent to retrenchment of workers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101497&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `No worker employed in any industry`
  line `who has been in continuous service for not less than one year under an employer shall be retrenched by`
  line `that employer until---`
  line
  line `(a) the worker has been given one month's notice in writing indicating the reasons for`
  line `retrenchment and the period of notice has expired, or the worker has been paid in lieu of such notice,`
  line `wages for the period of the notice;`
  line
  line `(b) the worker has been paid, at the time of retrenchment, compensation which shall be equivalent`
  line `to fifteen days' average pay, or average pay of such days as may be notified by the appropriate`
  line `Government, for every completed year of continuous service or any part thereof in excess of six`
  line `months; and`
  line
  line `(c) notice in such manner as may be prescribed is served on the appropriate Government or such`
  line `authority as may be specified by the appropriate Government by notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (101498)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Procedure for retrenchment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101498&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `Where any worker in an industrial establishment who is a`
  line `citizen of India, is to be retrenched and he belongs to a particular category of workers in that`
  line `establishment, then, in the absence of any agreement between the employer and the worker in this`
  line `behalf, the employer shall ordinarily retrench the worker who was the last person to be employed in`
  line `that category, unless for reasons to be recorded the employer retrenches any other worker.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (101499)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Re-employment of retrenched worker.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101499&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `Where any worker is retrenched and the employer`
  line `proposes to take into his employment any person within one year of such retrenchment, he shall, in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed, give an opportunity to the retrenched workers who are citizens of India`
  line `to offer themselves for re-employment and such retrenched workers who offer themselves for reemployment shall have preference over other persons.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (101500)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Compensation to workers in case of transfer of establishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101500&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `Where the ownership or`
  line `management of an establishment is transferred, whether by agreement or by operation of law, from the`
  line `employer in relation to that establishment to a new employer, every worker who has been in continuous`
  line `service for not less than one year in that establishment immediately before such transfer shall be entitled`
  line `to notice and compensation in accordance with the provisions of section 70 as if the worker had been`
  line `retrenched:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to a worker in any case where there has been a`
  line `change of employers by reason of the transfer, if---`
  line
  line `(a) the service of the worker has not been interrupted by such transfer;`
  line
  line `(b) the terms and conditions of service applicable to the worker after such transfer are not in any`
  line `way less favourable to the worker than those applicable to them immediately before the transfer; and`
  line
  line `(c) the new employer is, under the terms of such transfer or otherwise, legally liable to pay to the`
  line `worker, in the event of his retrenchment, compensation on the basis that his service has been`
  line `continuous and has not been interrupted by the transfer.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (101501)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Sixty days’ notice to be given of intention to close down any undertaking.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101501&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) An employer`
  line `who intends to close down an undertaking shall serve, at least sixty days before the date on which the`
  line `intended closure is to become effective, a notice, in such manner as may be prescribed, on the`
  line `appropriate Government stating clearly the reasons for the intended closure of the undertaking:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to---`
  line
  line `(i) an industrial establishment in which less than fifty workers are employed or were employed`
  line `on any day in the preceding twelve months;`
  line
  line `(ii) an industrial establishment set up for the construction of buildings, bridges, roads, canals,`
  line `dams or for other construction work or project.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the appropriate Government may, if it is`
  line `satisfied that owing to such exceptional circumstances as accident in the undertaking or death of the`
  line `employer or an extraordinary situation such as natural calamities or the like, it is necessary so to do, by`
  line `order, direct that the provisions of sub-section (1) shall not apply in relation to such undertaking for`
  line `such period, as may be specified in the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (101502)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Compensation to workers in case of closing down of undertakings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101502&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an`
  line `establishment is closed down for any reason whatsoever, every worker who has been in continuous`
  line `service for not less than one year in that undertaking immediately before such closure shall, subject to`
  line `the provisions of sub-section (2), be entitled to notice and compensation in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of section 70, as if the worker had been retrenched:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the undertaking is closed down on account of unavoidable circumstances`
  line `beyond the control of the employer, the compensation to be paid to the worker under clause (b) of`
  line `section 70, shall not exceed his average pay for three months.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---An industrial establishment which is closed down by reason merely of---`
  line
  line `(i) financial difficulties (including financial losses); or`
  line
  line `(ii) accumulation of un-disposed stocks; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the expiry of the period of the lease or license granted to it; or`
  line
  line `(iv) in case where the undertaking is engaged in mining operations, exhaustion of the minerals in`
  line `the area in which operations are carried on,`
  line
  line `shall not be deemed to be closed down on account of unavoidable circumstances beyond the control of`
  line `the employer within the meaning of the proviso to this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an undertaking engaged in mining`
  line `operations is closed down by reason merely of exhaustion of the minerals in the area in which such`
  line `operations are carried on, no worker referred to in that sub-section shall be entitled to any notice or`
  line `compensation in accordance with the provisions of section 70, if---`
  line
  line `(a) the employer provides the worker, at the place located within a radius of twenty kilometres`
  line `from such undertaking engaged in mining operation is closed down, with alternative employment`
  line `with effect from the date of closure at the same remuneration as he was entitled to receive, and on`
  line `the same terms and conditions of service as were applicable to him, immediately before the closure;`
  line
  line `(b) the service of the worker has not been interrupted by such alternative employment; and (c)`
  line `the employer is, under the terms of such alternative employment or otherwise, legally liable to pay`
  line `to the worker, in the event of his retrenchment, compensation on the basis that his service has been`
  line `continuous and has not been interrupted by such alternative employment.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of sub-sections (1) and (2), the expressions "minerals" and "mining operations"`
  line `shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in clauses (a) and (d) of section 3 of the Mines`
  line `and Minerals (Regulation and Development) Act, 1957 (67 of 1957).`
  line
  line `(4) Where any undertaking set up for the construction of buildings, bridges, roads, canals, dams or`
  line `other construction work is closed down on account of the completion of the work within two years from`
  line `the date on which the undertaking had been set up, no worker employed therein shall be entitled to any`
  line `compensation under clause (b) of section 70, but if the construction work is not so completed within`
  line `two years, he shall be entitled to notice and compensation under that section for every completed year`
  line `of continuous service or any part thereof in excess of six months.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (101503)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Effect of laws inconsistent with this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101503&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Chapter shall have`
  line `effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law including standing`
  line `orders made under Chapter IV: Provided that where under the provisions of any other Act or rules,`
  line `orders or notifications issued thereunder or under any standing orders or any award, contract or service`
  line `or otherwise, a worker is entitled to benefits in respect of any matter which are more favourable to him`
  line `than those to which he would be entitled under this Code, the worker shall continue to be entitled to the`
  line `more favourable benefits in respect of that matter, notwithstanding that he receives benefits in respect`
  line `of other matters under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that nothing contained in this Chapter shall be`
  line `deemed to affect the provisions of any other law for the time being in force in any State in so far as that`
  line `law provides for the settlement of industrial disputes, but the rights and liabilities of employers and`
  line `workers in so far as they relate to lay-off and retrenchment shall be determined in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (101504)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Application of this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101504&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Chapter shall apply to an industrial`
  line `establishment (not being an establishment of a seasonal character or in which work is performed only`
  line `intermittently) in which not less than three hundred workers, or such higher number of workers as may`
  line `be notified by the appropriate Government, were employed on an average per working day in the`
  line `preceding twelve months.`
  line
  line `(2) If a question arises whether an industrial establishment is of a seasonal character or whether work`
  line `is performed therein only intermittently, the decision of the appropriate Government thereon shall be`
  line final.
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of this Chapter, "industrial establishment" means---`
  line
  line `(i) a factory as defined in clause (m) of section 2 of the Factories Act, 1948 (63 of 1948);`
  line
  line `(ii) a mine as defined in clause (j) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Mines Act, 1952`
  line `(35 of 1952); or`
  line
  line `(iii) a plantation as defined in clause (f) of section 2 of the Plantations Labour Act, 1951`
  line `(69 of 1951).`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (101505)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Prohibition of lay-off.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101505&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `(1) No worker (other than a badli worker or a casual worker) whose`
  line `name is borne on the muster rolls of an industrial establishment to which this Chapter applies shall be`
  line `laid-off by his employer except with the prior permission of the appropriate Government, obtained on`
  line `an application made in this behalf, unless such lay-off is due to shortage of power, natural calamity, and`
  line `in the case of a mine, such lay-off is due to fire, flood, excess of inflammable gas or explosion.`
  line
  line `(2) An application for permission under sub-section (1) shall be made by the employer electronically`
  line `or otherwise in the prescribed manner stating clearly the reasons for the intended lay-off and a copy of`
  line `such application shall also be served simultaneously on the workers concerned in such manner as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the workers (other than badli workers or casual workers) of industrial establishment,`
  line `being a mine, have been laid-off under sub-section (1) for reasons of fire, flood or excess of inflammable`
  line `gas or explosion, the employer, in relation to such establishment, shall, within a period of thirty days`
  line `from the date of commencement of such lay-off, apply, in such manner as may be prescribed, to the`
  line `appropriate Government for permission to continue the lay-off.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an application for permission under sub-section (1) or sub-section (3) has been made, the`
  line `appropriate Government, after making such enquiry as it thinks fit and after giving a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard to the employer, the workers concerned and the persons interested in such`
  line `lay-off, may, having regard to the genuineness and adequacy of the reasons for such lay-off, the interests`
  line `of the workers and all other relevant factors, by order and for reasons to be recorded in writing, grant`
  line `or refuse to grant such permission and a copy of such order shall be communicated to the employer and`
  line `the workers.`
  line
  line `(5) Where an application for permission under sub-section (1) or sub-section (3) has been made and`
  line `the appropriate Government does not communicate the order granting or refusing to grant permission`
  line `to the employer within a period of sixty days from the date on which such application is made, the`
  line `permission applied for shall be deemed to have been granted as applied for on the expiration of the said`
  line `period of sixty days and the application shall be deemed to have been disposed of accordingly by the`
  line `appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(6) An order of the appropriate Government granting or refusing to grant permission shall, subject`
  line `to the provisions of sub-section (7), be final and binding on all the parties concerned and shall remain`
  line `in force for one year from the date of such order.`
  line
  line `(7) The appropriate Government may, either on its own motion or on the application made by the`
  line `employer or any worker, review its order granting or refusing to grant permission under sub-section (4)`
  line `within the prescribed time from the date on which such order is made or refer the matter or, as the case`
  line `may be, cause it to be referred, to a Tribunal for adjudication:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a reference has been made to a Tribunal under this sub-section, it shall pass an`
  line `award within a period of thirty days from the date of such reference.`
  line
  line `(8) Where no application for permission under sub-section (1) is made, or where no application for`
  line `permission under sub-section (3) is made within the period specified therein, or where the permission`
  line `for any lay-off has been refused, such lay-off shall be deemed to be illegal from the date on which the`
  line `workers had been laid-off and the workers shall be entitled to all the benefits under any law for the time`
  line `being in force as if they had not been laid-off.`
  line
  line `(9) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this section, the appropriate`
  line `Government may, if it is satisfied that owing to such exceptional circumstances as accident in the`
  line `establishment or death of the employer or the like, it is necessary so to do, by order, direct that the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (1), or, as the case may be, sub-section (3) shall not apply in relation to such`
  line `establishment for such period as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(10) The provisions of section 67 (other than the second proviso thereto) shall apply to cases of layoff referred to in this section.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this section, a worker shall not be deemed to be laid-off by an`
  line `employer if such employer offers any alternative employment (which in the opinion of the employer`
  line `does not call for any special skill or previous experience and can be done by the worker) in the same`
  line `establishment from which he has been laid-off or in any other establishment belonging to the same`
  line `employer, situate in the same town or village, or situate within such distance from the establishment to`
  line `which he belongs that the transfer will not involve undue hardship to the worker having regard to the`
  line `facts and circumstances of his case, subject to the condition that the wages which would normally have`
  line `been paid to the worker are offered for the alternative appointment also.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (101506)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Conditions precedent to retrenchment of workers to which Chapter X applies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101506&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) No`
  line `worker employed in any industrial establishment to which this Chapter applies, who has been in`
  line `continuous service for not less than one year under an employer shall be retrenched by that employer`
  line until,---
  line
  line `(a) the worker has been given three month’s notice in writing indicating the reasons for`
  line `retrenchment and the period of notice has expired, or the worker has been paid in lieu of such notice,`
  line `wages for the period of the notice; and`
  line
  line `(b) the prior permission of the appropriate Government has been obtained on an application made`
  line `in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) An application for permission under sub-section (1) shall be made by the employer electronically`
  line `or otherwise in the prescribed manner stating clearly the reasons for the intended retrenchment and a`
  line `copy of such application shall also be served simultaneously on the workers concerned in such manner`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an application for permission under sub-section (1) has been made, the appropriate`
  line `Government, after making such enquiry as it thinks fit and after giving a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `being heard to the employer, the workers concerned and the persons interested in such retrenchment,`
  line `may, having regard to the genuineness and adequacy of the reasons stated by the employer, the interests`
  line `of the workers and all other relevant factors, by order and for reasons to be recorded in writing, grant`
  line `or refuse to grant such permission and a copy of such order shall be communicated to the employer and`
  line `the workers.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an application for permission has been made under sub-section (1) and the appropriate`
  line `Government does not communicate the order granting or refusing to grant permission to the employer`
  line `within a period of sixty days from the date on which such application is made, the permission applied`
  line `for shall be deemed to have been granted on the expiration of the said period of sixty days and the`
  line `application shall be deemed to have been disposed of accordingly by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(5) An order of the appropriate Government granting or refusing to grant permission shall, subject`
  line `to the provisions of sub-section (6), be final and binding on all the parties concerned and shall remain`
  line `in force for one year from the date of such order.`
  line
  line `(6) The appropriate Government may, either on its own motion or on the application made by the`
  line `employer or any worker, review its order granting or refusing to grant permission under sub-section (3)`
  line `within the prescribed time from the date on which such order is made or refer the matter or, as the case`
  line `may be, cause it to be referred to a Tribunal for adjudication:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a reference has been made to a Tribunal under this sub-section, it shall pass an`
  line `award within a period of thirty days from the date of such reference.`
  line
  line `(7) Where no application for permission under sub-section (1) is made, or where the permission for`
  line `any retrenchment has been refused, such retrenchment shall be deemed to be illegal from the date on`
  line `which the notice of retrenchment was given to the worker and the worker shall be entitled to all the`
  line `benefits under any law for the time being in force as if no notice had been given to him.`
  line
  line `(8) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this section, the appropriate`
  line `Government may, if it is satisfied that owing to such exceptional circumstances as accident in the`
  line `establishment or death of the employer or the like, it is necessary so to do, by order, direct that the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (1) shall not apply in relation to such establishment for such period as may be`
  line `specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(9) Where permission for retrenchment has been granted under sub-section (3) or where permission`
  line `for retrenchment is deemed to be granted under sub-section (4), every worker who is employed in that`
  line `establishment immediately before the date of application for permission under this section shall be`
  line `entitled to receive, at the time of retrenchment, compensation which shall be equivalent to fifteen days`
  line `average pay, or average pay of such days as may be notified by the appropriate Government, for every`
  line `completed year of continuous service or any part thereof, in excess of six months.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (101507)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Procedure for closing down an industrial establishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101507&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `(1) An employer who intends to`
  line `close down an undertaking of an industrial establishment to which this Chapter applies shall,`
  line `electronically or otherwise, apply in such manner as may be prescribed, for prior permission at least`
  line `ninety days before the date on which the intended closure is to become effective, to the appropriate`
  line `Government, stating clearly the reasons for the intended closure of the undertaking and a copy of such`
  line `application shall also be served simultaneously on the representatives of the workers in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to an undertaking set up for the construction of`
  line `buildings, bridges, roads, canals, dams or for other construction work.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an application for permission has been made under sub-section (1), the appropriate`
  line `Government, after making such enquiry as it thinks fit and after giving a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `being heard to the employer, the workers and the persons interested in such closure may, having regard`
  line `to the genuineness and adequacy of the reasons stated by the employer, the interests of the general`
  line `public and all other relevant factors, by order and for reasons to be recorded in writing, grant or refuse`
  line `to grant such permission and a copy of such order shall be communicated to the employer and the`
  line workers.
  line
  line `(3) Where an application has been made under sub-section (1) and the appropriate Government does`
  line `not communicate the order granting or refusing to grant permission to the employer within a period of`
  line `sixty days from the date on which such application is made, the permission applied for shall be deemed`
  line `to have been granted as applied for on the expiration of the said period of sixty days and the application`
  line `shall be deemed to have been disposed of accordingly by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(4) An order of the appropriate Government granting or refusing to grant permission shall, subject`
  line `to the provisions of sub-section (5), be final and binding on all the parties and shall remain in force for`
  line `one year from the date of such order.`
  line
  line `(5) The appropriate Government may, either on its own motion or on the application made by the`
  line `employer or any worker, review its order granting or refusing to grant permission under sub-section (2)`
  line `within the prescribed time from the date on which such order is made or refer the matter to a Tribunal`
  line `for adjudication:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a reference has been made to a Tribunal under this sub-section, it shall pass an`
  line `award within a period of thirty days from the date of such reference.`
  line
  line `(6) Where no application for permission under sub-section (1) is made within the period specified`
  line `therein, or where the permission for closure has been refused, the closure of the undertaking shall be`
  line `deemed to be illegal from the date of closure and the workers shall be entitled to all the benefits under`
  line `any law for the time being in force as if the undertaking had not been closed down.`
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this section, the appropriate`
  line `Government may, if it is satisfied that owing to such exceptional circumstances as accident in the`
  line `undertaking or death of the employer or the like it is necessary so to do, by order, direct that the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (1) shall not apply in relation to such undertaking for such period as may be`
  line `specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(8) Where an undertaking is permitted to be closed down under sub-section (2) or where permission`
  line `for closure is deemed to be granted under sub-section (3), every worker who is employed in that`
  line `undertaking immediately before the date of application for permission under this section, shall be`
  line `entitled to receive compensation which shall be equivalent to fifteen days average pay, or average pay`
  line `of such days as may be notified by the appropriate Government, for every completed year of continuous`
  line `service or any part thereof in excess of six months.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (101508)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Duty of an employer to maintain muster rolls of workers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101508&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding that workers in`
  line `any industrial establishment have been laid-off, it shall be the duty of every employer to maintain for`
  line `the purposes of this Chapter a muster roll, and to provide for the making of entries therein by workers`
  line `who may present themselves for work at the establishment at the appointed time during normal working`
  line hours.
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (102037)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Certain provisions of Chapter IX to apply to industrial establishment to which this Chapter applies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=102037&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of sections 66, 71, 72, 73 and section 76 in Chapter IX shall, so far as may`
  line `be, apply also in relation to an industrial establishment to which the provisions of this Chapter apply.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (101510)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Worker re-skilling fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101510&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government shall, by notification, set up a fund`
  line `to be called the worker re-skilling fund (hereafter in this section referred to as "fund").`
  line
  line `(2) The fund shall consist of---`
  line
  line `(a) the contribution of the employer of an industrial establishment an amount equal to fifteen`
  line `days wages last drawn by the worker immediately before the retrenchment, or such other number of`
  line `days as may be notified by the Central Government, for every retrenched worker in case of`
  line `retrenchment only;`
  line
  line `(b) the contribution from such other sources as may be prescribed by the appropriate`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) The fund shall be utilised by crediting fifteen days wages last drawn by the worker to his account`
  line `who is retrenched, within forty-five days of such retrenchment, in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (101511)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Prohibition of unfair labour practice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101511&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `No employer or worker or a Trade Union, whether`
  line `registered under this Code, or not, shall commit any unfair labour practice specified in the Second`
  line Schedule.
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (101512)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Power of officers of appropriate Government to impose penalty in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101512&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 84, for the purpose of imposing penalty under subsections (3), (5), (7), (8), (9), (10), (11) and (20) of section 86 and sub-section (7) of section 89, the`
  line `appropriate Government may appoint any officer not below the rank of Under Secretary to the`
  line `Government of India or an officer of equivalent rank in the State Government, as the case may be, for`
  line `holding enquiry in such manner, as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) While holding the enquiry, the officer referred to in sub-section (1) shall have the power to`
  line `summon and enforce attendance of any person acquainted with the facts and circumstances of the case`
  line `to give evidence or to produce any document, which in the opinion of such officer, may be useful for`
  line `or relevant to the subject matter of the enquiry and if, on such enquiry, he is satisfied that the person`
  line `has committed any offence under the provisions referred to in sub-section (1), he may impose such`
  line `penalty as he thinks fit in accordance with such provisions.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a person fails to pay the penalty referred to in sub-section (2) within a period of ninety`
  line `days from the date of receipt of the copy of the order, he shall be punishable with fine which shall not`
  line `be less than fifty thousand rupees but may extend up to two lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (101513)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101513&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `(1) An employer who contravenes the provisions of section 78 or section 79 or`
  line `section 80 shall be punishable with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees, but which may`
  line `extend to ten lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) An employer who after conviction for an offence under section 78 or section 79 or section 80`
  line `again commits the same offence under section 78 or section 79 or section 80, then, he shall for the`
  line `second or subsequent offence be punishable with fine which shall not be less than five lakh rupees, but`
  line `which may extend up to twenty lakh rupees or with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six`
  line `months, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) An employer who contravenes the provisions of section 67 or section 70 or section 73 or section`
  line `75 shall be punishable with fine which shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees, but which may`
  line `extend to two lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(4) An employer who after conviction for an offence under section 67 or section 70 or section 73 or`
  line `section 75 again commits the same offence under section 67 or section 70 or section 73 or section 75,`
  line `then, he shall for the second or subsequent offence be punishable with fine which shall not be less than`
  line `one lakh rupees, but which may extend to five lakh rupees or with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to six months, or with both.`
  line
  line `(5) Any person who commits any unfair labour practice as specified in the Second Schedule shall`
  line `be punishable with fine which shall not be less than ten thousand rupees, but which may extend to two`
  line `lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(6) Any person who after conviction for any unfair labour practice again commits the same offence,`
  line `then, he shall, for committing the second or subsequent offence, be punishable with fine which shall`
  line `not be less than fifty thousand rupees, but which may extend to five lakh rupees or with imprisonment`
  line `for a term which may extend to three months, or with both.`
  line
  line `(7) If default is made on the part of any registered Trade Union in giving any notice or sending any`
  line `statement or other document as required by or under any of the provisions of this Code, every officebearer or other person bound by the rules of the Trade Union to give or send the same, or, if there is no`
  line `such office-bearer or person, every member of the executive of the Trade Union, shall be punishable`
  line `with fine which shall not be less than one thousand rupees, but which may extend to ten thousand rupees`
  line `and any continuing default shall be punishable with an additional penalty of fifty rupees per day so long`
  line `as the default continues.`
  line
  line `(8) Any person who wilfully makes, or causes to be made, any false entry in, or any omission from,`
  line `the general statement required by section 26 or in or from any copy of rules or of alterations of rules`
  line `sent to the Registrar under that section, shall be punishable with fine which shall not be less than two`
  line `thousand rupees, but which may extend to twenty thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(9) Any person who, with intent to deceive, gives to any member of a registered Trade Union or to`
  line `any person intending or applying to become a member of such Trade Union any document purporting`
  line `to be a copy of the rules of the Trade Union or of any alterations to the same which he knows, or has`
  line `reason to believe, is not a correct copy of such rules or alterations as are for the time being in force, or`
  line `any person who, with the intent, gives a copy of any rules of an unregistered Trade Union to any person`
  line `on the pretence that such rules are the rules of a registered Trade Union, shall be punishable with fine`
  line `which shall not be less than five thousand rupees, but which may extend to twenty thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(10) An employer who fails to submit draft standing orders as required by section 30, or who`
  line `modifies his standing orders otherwise than in accordance with section 35, shall be punishable with fine`
  line `which shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees, but which may extend to two lakh rupees and in the`
  line `case of a continuing offence with an additional fine of two thousand rupees per day till the offence`
  line continues.
  line
  line `(11) An employer who does any act in contravention of the standing orders finally certified under`
  line `this Code shall be punishable with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees, but which may`
  line `extend to two lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(12) Any person who after conviction under sub-section (11) again commits the same offence, then,`
  line `he shall, for committing the second or subsequent offence be punishable with fine which shall not be`
  line `less than two lakh rupees, but which may extend to four lakh rupees or with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to three months, or with both.`
  line
  line `(13) Any worker who commences, continues or otherwise acts in furtherance of a strike which is`
  line `illegal under this Code, shall be punishable with fine which shall not be less than one thousand rupees,`
  line `but which may extend up to ten thousand rupees or with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `one month, or with both.`
  line
  line `(14) Any employer who commences, continues, or otherwise acts in furtherance of a lock-out which`
  line `is illegal under this Code, shall be punishable with fine which shall not be less than fifty thousand`
  line `rupees, but which may extend to one lakh rupees or with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `one month, or with both.`
  line
  line `(15) Any person who instigates or incites others to take part in, or otherwise acts in furtherance of,`
  line `a strike or lock-out which is illegal under this Code, shall be punishable with fine which shall not be`
  line `less than ten thousand rupees, but which may extend to fifty thousand rupees or with imprisonment for`
  line `a term which may extend to one month, or with both.`
  line
  line `(16) Any person who knowingly spends or applies any money in direct furtherance or support of`
  line `any illegal strike or lock-out shall be punishable with fine which shall not be less than ten thousand`
  line `rupees, but which may extend to fifty thousand rupees or with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to one month, or with both.`
  line
  line `(17) Any person who commits a breach of any term of any settlement or award, which is binding on`
  line `him under this Code, shall be punishable with fine which shall not be less than twenty thousand rupees,`
  line `but which may extend to two lakh rupees or with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three`
  line `months, or with both.`
  line
  line `(18) Where the breach under sub-section (17) is a continuing one, the offender shall be punishable`
  line `with an additional fine which may extend to one thousand rupees for every day during which the breach`
  line `continues after the first conviction and the court trying the offence, if it fines the offender, may direct`
  line `that the whole or any part of the fine realised from him shall be paid, by way of compensation, to any`
  line `person who, in its opinion, has been affected by such breach.`
  line
  line `(19) Any person who wilfully discloses any such information as is referred to in section 61 in`
  line `contravention of the provisions of that section shall, on a complaint made by or on behalf of the Trade`
  line `Union or individual business affected, be punishable with fine which may extend to twenty thousand`
  line `rupees, or with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one month, or with both.`
  line
  line `(20) Any person who contravenes any other provision of this Code not covered under sub-sections`
  line `(1) to (19) or the rules or regulations framed under this Code shall be punishable with fine which may`
  line `extend to one lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (101514)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101514&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) No court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under`
  line `this Code, save on a complaint made by or under the authority of the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), no`
  line `court inferior to that of the Metropolitan Magistrate or Judicial Magistrate of the first class shall try the`
  line `offences under this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (101515)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101515&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the person committing an offence under this Code is a company,`
  line `every person who, at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible to, the`
  line `company for the conduct of business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge and that he exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Code has`
  line `been committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this section,---`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes---`
  line
  line `(i) a firm; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a limited liability partnership registered under the Limited Liability Partnership Act,`
  line `2008 (6 of 2009); or`
  line
  line `(iii) other association of individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director" in relation to a firm means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (101516)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Composition of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101516&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), any offence punishable under this Code, not being an offence punishable`
  line `with imprisonment only, or with imprisonment and also with fine, may, on an application of the accused`
  line `person, either before or after the institution of any prosecution, be compounded by a Gazetted Officer,`
  line `as the appropriate Government may, by notification, specify, for a sum of fifty per cent. of the maximum`
  line `fine provided for such offence punishable with fine only and for a sum of seventy-five per cent.`
  line
  line `provided for such offence punishable with imprisonment for a term which is not more than one year`
  line `or with fine, in the manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that such amount of composition shall be credited to the Social Security Fund established`
  line `under section 141 of the Social Security Code, 2020.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall apply to an offence committed by a person for the`
  line `second time or thereafter within a period of three years from the date---`
  line
  line `(a) of commission of a similar offence which was earlier compounded;`
  line
  line `(b) of commission of similar offence for which such person was earlier convicted.`
  line
  line `(3) Every officer referred to in sub-section (1) shall exercise the powers to compound an offence,`
  line `subject to the direction, control and supervision of the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Every application for the compounding of an offence shall be made in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(5) Where any offence is compounded before the institution of any prosecution, no prosecution shall`
  line `be instituted in relation to such offence, against the offender in relation to whom the offence is so`
  line compounded.
  line
  line `(6) Where the composition of any offence is made after the institution of any prosecution, such`
  line `composition shall be brought by the officer referred to in sub-section (1) in writing, to the notice of the`
  line `adjudicating officer appointed under sub-section (1) of section 85 before whom the prosecution is`
  line `pending and on such notice of the composition of the offence being given, the person against whom the`
  line `offence is so compounded shall be discharged.`
  line
  line `(7) Any person who fails to comply with an order made by the officer referred to in sub-section (1),`
  line `shall be liable to pay a sum equivalent to twenty per cent. of the maximum fine provided for the offence,`
  line `in addition to such fine.`
  line
  line `(8) No offence punishable under the provisions of this Code shall be compounded except under and`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (102038)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Conditions of service, etc., to remain unchanged under certain circumstances during pendency of proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=102038&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an industrial dispute pertaining to an establishment or`
  line `undertaking is already pending before a conciliation officer or an Arbitrator or a Tribunal or a National`
  line `Industrial Tribunal, as the case may be, with regard to matters not covered by the notice of change`
  line `issued by an employer under section 40, no employer shall---`
  line
  line `(a) in regard to any matter connected with such dispute, alter to the prejudice of the workers`
  line `concerned in such dispute the conditions of service applicable to them immediately before the`
  line `commencement of such proceedings; or`
  line
  line `(b) for any misconduct connected with the dispute, discharge or punish, whether by dismissal or`
  line `otherwise any worker concerned in such dispute,`
  line
  line `save with the express permission in writing of the authority before which the proceeding is pending.`
  line
  line `(2) During the pendency of any such proceeding in respect of an industrial dispute referred in subsection (1), the employer may, in accordance with standing orders applicable to a worker concerned in`
  line `such dispute or, where there are no such standing orders, in accordance with the terms of the contract,`
  line `whether express or implied, between him and the worker---`
  line
  line `(a) alter, in regard to any matter not connected with the dispute, the conditions of service`
  line `applicable to that worker immediately before the commencement of such proceeding; or`
  line
  line `(b) for any misconduct not connected with the dispute, discharge or punish, whether by dismissal`
  line `or otherwise, that worker:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such worker shall be discharged or dismissed, unless he has been paid wages for`
  line `one month and an application has been made by the employer to the authority before which the`
  line `proceeding is pending for approval of the action taken by the employer.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), no employer shall, during the pendency`
  line `of any proceeding in respect of an industrial dispute, take any action against any protected worker`
  line `concerned in such dispute---`
  line
  line `(a) by altering, to the prejudice of such protected worker, the conditions of service applicable to`
  line `him immediately before the commencement of such proceeding; or`
  line
  line `(b) by discharging or punishing, whether by dismissal or otherwise, such protected worker,`
  line
  line `save with the express permission in writing of the authority before which the proceeding is pending.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this sub-section, a "protected worker" in relation to an`
  line `establishment, means a worker who, being a member of the executive or other office-bearer of a`
  line `registered Trade Union connected with the establishment, is recognised as such in accordance with rules`
  line `made in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(4) In every establishment, the number of workers to be recognised as protected workers for the`
  line `purposes of sub-section (3) shall be one per cent. of the total number of workers employed therein`
  line `subject to a minimum number of five protected workers and a maximum number of one hundred`
  line `protected workers and for the aforesaid purpose, the appropriate Government may make rules providing`
  line `for the distribution of such protected workers among various Trade Unions, if any, connected with the`
  line `establishment and the manner in which the workers may be chosen and recognised as protected workers.`
  line
  line `(5) Where an employer makes an application to conciliation officer, arbitrator, Tribunal or National`
  line `Industrial Tribunal, as the case may be, under the proviso to sub-section (2) for approval of the action`
  line `taken by him, the authority concerned shall, without delay, hear such application and pass, within a`
  line `period of three months from the date of receipt of such application, such order in relation thereto as it`
  line `deems fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any such authority considers it necessary or expedient so to do, it may, for`
  line `reasons to be recorded in writing, extend such period by such further periods as it may think fit:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no proceedings before any such authority shall lapse merely on the ground that`
  line `any period specified in this sub-section had expired without such proceedings being completed.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (102039)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Special provision for adjudication as to whether conditions of service, etc., changed during pendency of proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=102039&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `Where an employer contravenes the provisions of section 90 during the`
  line `pendency of proceedings before conciliation officer, arbitrator, Tribunal or National Industrial Tribunal,`
  line `as the case may be, any employee aggrieved by such contravention, may make a complaint in writing`
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed---`
  line
  line `(a) to such conciliation officer, and the conciliation officer shall take such complaint into account`
  line `in mediating in, and promoting the settlement of, such industrial dispute; and`
  line
  line `(b) to such arbitrator, Tribunal or National Industrial Tribunal and on receipt of such complaint,`
  line `the arbitrator, Tribunal or National Industrial Tribunal, as the case may be, shall adjudicate upon the`
  line `complaint as if it were a dispute referred to or pending before it, in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of this Code and shall submit his or its award to the appropriate Government and the provisions of`
  line `this Code shall apply accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (101519)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Power to transfer certain proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101519&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may, by order in`
  line `writing and for reasons to be stated therein, withdraw any proceeding under this Code pending before`
  line `a Tribunal and transfer the same to another Tribunal, as the case may be, for the disposal of the`
  line `proceeding and the Tribunal to which the proceeding is so transferred may, subject to special directions`
  line `in the order of transfer, proceed either de novo or from the stage at which it was so transferred.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by order in writing and for reasons to be stated therein, withdraw`
  line `any proceeding pending under this Code before a Tribunal constituted by the Central Government or`
  line `the State Government and transfer to a National Industrial Tribunal for disposal of the proceeding and`
  line `the National Industrial Tribunal to which the proceeding is so transferred may, subject to special`
  line `directions in the order of transfer, proceed either de novo or from the stage at which it was so transferred.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by notification, and for reasons to be stated therein, empower a`
  line `Tribunal constituted by the State Government to entertain and dispose of the cases arising within their`
  line `respective jurisdiction under the provisions of this Code where the appropriate Government is the`
  line `Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (101520)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Protection of persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101520&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person refusing to take part or to continue to take part in any`
  line `strike or lock-out which is illegal under this Code shall, by reason of such refusal or by reason of any`
  line `action taken by him under this section, be subject to expulsion from any Trade Union or society, or to`
  line `any fine or penalty, or to deprivation of any right or benefit to which he or his legal representatives`
  line `would otherwise be entitled, or be liable to be placed in any respect, either directly or indirectly, under`
  line `any disability or at any disadvantage as compared with other members of the Union or society, anything`
  line `to the contrary in rules of a Trade Union or society notwithstanding.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in the rules of a Trade Union or society requiring the settlement of dispute in any manner`
  line `shall apply to any proceeding for enforcing any right or exemption secured by this section, and in any`
  line `such proceeding the civil court may, in lieu of ordering a person who has been expelled from`
  line `membership of a Trade Union or society to be restored to membership, order that he be paid out of the`
  line `funds of the Trade Union or society such sum by way of compensation or damages as that court thinks`
  line just.
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (101521)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Representation of parties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101521&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `(1) A worker who is a party to a dispute shall be entitled to be`
  line `represented in any proceeding under this Code by---`
  line
  line `(a) any member of the executive or other office-bearer of a registered Trade Union of which`
  line `he is a member;`
  line
  line `(b) any member of the executive or other office-bearer of a federation of Trade Unions to`
  line `which the Trade Union referred to in clause (a) is affiliated;`
  line
  line `(c) where the worker is not a member of any Trade Union, any member of the executive or`
  line `other office-bearer of any Trade Union connected with, or by any other worker employed in the`
  line `industry in which the worker is employed and authorised in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) An employer who is a party to a dispute shall be entitled to be represented in any proceeding`
  line `under this Code by---`
  line
  line `(a) an officer of an association of employer of which he is a member;`
  line
  line `(b) an officer of a federation of associations of employers to which the association referred`
  line `to in clause (a) is affiliated;`
  line
  line `(c) where the employer is not a member of any association of employers, an officer of any`
  line `association of employers connected with, or by any other employer engaged in, the industry in`
  line `which the employer is engaged and authorised in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) No party to a dispute shall be entitled to be represented by a legal practitioner in any conciliation`
  line `proceedings under this Code or any proceedings before Tribunal or National Industrial Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (3), in any proceeding before a Tribunal or`
  line `a National Industrial Tribunal, a party to a dispute may be represented by a legal practitioner with the`
  line `consent of the other parties to the proceeding and with the leave of the Tribunal or National Industrial`
  line `Tribunal, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (101522)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Removal of doubts in interpretation of award or settlement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101522&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, in the opinion of the`
  line `appropriate Government, any difficulty or doubt arises as to the interpretation of any provision of an`
  line `award or settlement, it may refer the question to such Tribunal or National Industrial Tribunal as it may`
  line `think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) A Tribunal or National Industrial Tribunal to which such question is referred shall, after giving`
  line `the parties an opportunity of being heard, decide such question and its decision shall be final and binding`
  line `on all such parties.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (101523)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Power to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101523&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the appropriate Government is satisfied in relation to any`
  line `industrial establishment or undertaking or any class of industrial establishments or undertakings that`
  line `adequate provisions exist to fulfil the objects of any provision of this Code, it may, by notification,`
  line `exempt, conditionally or unconditionally such establishment or undertaking or, class of establishments`
  line `or undertakings from that provision of this Code.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where the appropriate Government is`
  line `satisfied in relation to any new industrial establishment or new undertaking or class of new industrial`
  line `establishments or new undertakings that it is necessary in the public interest so to do, it may, by`
  line `notification, exempt, conditionally or unconditionally, any such new establishment or new undertaking`
  line `or class of new establishments or new undertakings from all or any of the provisions of this Code for`
  line `such period from the date of establishment of such new industrial establishment or new undertaking or`
  line `class of new establishments or new undertakings, as the case may be, as may be specified in the`
  line `notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that any notification issued by a State Government under the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947`
  line `(14 of 1947), prior to the commencement of this Code, to achieve the purpose as is specified in this subsection in the State, shall remain in force after such commencement for its remaining period as if the`
  line `provisions of this Code have not been brought into force to the extent they defeat any purpose to be`
  line `achieved by such notification issued by that State Government.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "new industrial establishment or`
  line `new undertaking or class of new industrial establishments or new undertakings" means such industrial`
  line `establishment or undertaking or class of industrial establishments or undertakings which are established`
  line `within a period as may be specified in the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (101524)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title `Jurisdiction of civil courts barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101524&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction in respect of any`
  line `matter to which any provision of this Code applies and no injunction shall be granted by any civil court`
  line `in respect of anything which is done or intended to be done by or under this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (101525)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101525&sectionno=98&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against any person for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of`
  line `this Code or any rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (101526)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title `Power of appropriate Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101526&sectionno=99&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may,`
  line `subject to the condition of previous publication, make rules for the purpose of giving effect to the`
  line `provisions of this Code:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appropriate Government may, if it is satisfied that circumstances exist which render`
  line `it necessary or expedient in the public interest so to do, dispense with the condition of previous`
  line `publication or reduce the required time period for inviting objections or suggestions on such previous`
  line `publication to the extent as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) written agreement between the employer and worker arrived at otherwise than in the course`
  line `of conciliation proceeding to arrive at a settlement under clause (zi) of section 2;`
  line
  line `(b) constitution of Works Committee and choosing of representatives of employer and workers`
  line `engaged in the establishment under section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) manner of choosing members from the employer and the workers for Grievance Redressal`
  line `Committee under sub-section (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(d) application in respect of any dispute to be filed before the Grievance Redressal Committee`
  line `by any aggrieved worker under sub-section (5) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(e) manner of filing application for the conciliation of grievance as against the decision of the`
  line `Grievance Redressal Committee to the conciliation officer under sub-section (8) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(f) the payment of a subscription by members of the Trade Union and donation from such`
  line `members and others under clause (f) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(g) manner of annual audit under clause (j) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(h) form of declaration to be made by an affidavit and the manner of making the same under`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(i) general statement of the assets and liabilities of the Trade Union prepared in such form and`
  line `containing such particulars under sub-section (2) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(j) the form of application for registration under sub-section (1), and the form of issuing certificate`
  line `of registration to be issued by the Registrar to the applicant Trade Union under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 9;`
  line
  line `(k) the form of entering the name and other particulars of Trade Union in a register maintained`
  line `by the Registrar in this behalf under sub-section (3) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(l) verification of application of the Trade Union under sub-section (5) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(m) period within which appeal is to be preferred by Trade Union to Tribunal under sub-section`
  line `(1) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(n) sending of communication and notices under sub-section (1) and the manner to inform the`
  line `Registrar under sub-section (3) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(o) matters on which negotiating union or negotiating council, as the case may be, in an industrial`
  line `establishment may negotiate with the employer of the industrial establishment under sub-section (1)`
  line `and the criteria to be followed by the employer of industrial establishment under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 14;`
  line
  line `(p) manner of verification of workers on the muster roll of the industrial establishment, under`
  line `sub-sections (3) and (4) and the facilities to be provided by industrial establishment to a negotiating`
  line `union or negotiating council under sub-section (7) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(q) the objects under sub-section (1) and sub-section (2) and the subscription payable under subsection (4) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(r) manner of making application for adjudication before the Tribunal under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 22;`
  line
  line `(s) manner of amalgamation under sub-section (2), and the manner of sending signed`
  line `amalgamation to the Registrar of a different State under sub-section (3) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(t) distribution of funds of the Trade Union on dissolution by Registrar under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 25;`
  line
  line `(u) the date before which a general statement shall be forwarded annually to the Registrar, the`
  line `particulars to be contained in general statement and its form, the person by whom and the manner in`
  line `which such general statement shall be audited under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(v) manner and purpose of recognition of a Trade Union or a federation of Trade Unions by the`
  line `State Government as a State Trade Union at the State level and the authority and the manner of`
  line `deciding dispute by it under sub-section (2) of section 27;`
  line
  line `(w) the manner of forwarding information to the certifying officer under sub-section (3) of section`
  line `30 and the period within which the amendment of standing order is to be done as observed by the`
  line `certifying officer under the proviso thereof;`
  line
  line `(x) manner of choosing representatives of the workers of the industrial establishment or`
  line `undertaking for issuing notice by certifying officer, where there is no Trade Union operating, under`
  line `sub-section (5) and the manner of authentication of certified standing orders under sub-section (8)`
  line `of section 30;`
  line
  line `(y) statement to be accompanied with draft standing orders under sub-section (9) of section 30;`
  line
  line `(z) conditions for submission of draft standing orders by group of employers in similar`
  line `establishment under sub-section (10) of section 30;`
  line
  line `(za) manner of disposal of appeal by the appellate authority under section 32;`
  line
  line `(zb) the manner of sending copies of the order of the appellate authority under sub-section (1)`
  line `and the language and the manner of maintaining standing order under sub-section (2) of section 33;`
  line
  line `(zc) form of register for filing finally certified standing orders by the certifying officer and fee`
  line `for furnishing certified copy of such orders under section 34;`
  line
  line `(zd) application for modification of standing orders to be made before certifying officer under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 35;`
  line
  line `(ze) the manner of giving of notice of the nature of the change proposed to be effected under`
  line `clause (i) of section 40;`
  line
  line `(zf) form of arbitration agreement and the manner to be signed by the parties thereto under subsection (3) of section 42;`
  line
  line `(zg) manner of issuance of notification where an industrial dispute has been referred to`
  line `arbitration under sub-section (5) of section 42;`
  line
  line `(zh) manner of choosing representatives of the workers where there is no Trade Union under the`
  line `proviso to sub-section (5) of section 42;`
  line
  line `(zi) manner of filling up the vacancy under sub-section (9) of section 44;`
  line
  line `(zj) the procedure for selection, salaries and allowances and other terms and conditions of Judicial`
  line `and Administrative Members of the National Industrial Tribunal under sub-section (6) of section 46;`
  line
  line `(zk) such other matters in respect of which a conciliation officer, Tribunal and National Industrial`
  line `Tribunal shall have the same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure,1908 under sub-section (3) of section 49;`
  line
  line `(zl) manner of holding conciliation proceedings under sub-section (1), form of full report under`
  line `sub-section (4), and the form of application and the manner of deciding such application under subsection (6), of section 53;`
  line
  line `(zm) the number of persons by whom the notice of strike shall be given, the person or persons to`
  line `whom such notice shall be given, and the manner of giving such notice, under sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 62;`
  line
  line `(zn) manner of giving notice of lock-out under sub-section (5) and the authority under sub-section`
  line `(6) of section 62;`
  line
  line `(zo) manner of serving notice before retrenchment of a worker employed in the industry who has`
  line `been in continuous service for not less than one year by an employer on the appropriate Government`
  line `or such authority as may be specified by the appropriate Government by notification under clause`
  line `(c) of section 70;`
  line
  line `(zp) manner in which the employer shall give an opportunity to the retrenched workers who are`
  line `citizens of India to offer themselves for re-employment under section 72;`
  line
  line `(zq) manner in which the employer shall serve notice on the appropriate Government stating`
  line `clearly the reasons for the intended closure of the undertaking under sub-section (1) of section 74;`
  line
  line `(zr) manner of making application by the employer stating clearly the reasons for the intended`
  line `lay-off and the manner of serving copy of such application to workers under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 78;`
  line
  line `(zs) manner of applying to the appropriate Government for permission to continue the lay-off by`
  line `the employer under sub-section (3) of section 78;`
  line
  line `(zt) time-limit for review under sub-section (7) of section 78;`
  line
  line `(zu) manner of making application by the employer stating clearly the reasons for the intended`
  line `retrenchment and the manner of serving copy of such application to workers under sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 79;`
  line
  line `(zv) time-limit for review under sub-section (6) of section 79;`
  line
  line `(zw) manner of making application by the employer stating clearly the reasons for the intended`
  line `closing down of an undertaking of an industrial establishment and the manner of serving copy of`
  line `such application to the representatives of workers under sub-section (1) of section 80;`
  line
  line `(zx) time-limit for review under sub-section (5) of section 80;`
  line
  line `(zy) contribution from such other sources to be made to the worker re-skilling fund under clause`
  line `(b) of sub-section (2) of section 83;`
  line
  line `(zz) manner of utilisation of fund under sub-section (3) of section 83;`
  line
  line `(zza) manner of composition of offence by a Gazetted Officer specified under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 89;`
  line
  line `(zzb) manner of making application for the compounding of an offence specified under subsection (4) of section 89;`
  line
  line `(zzc) manner of making complaint by an aggrieved employee under section 91;`
  line
  line `(zzd) manner of authorisation of worker for representing in any proceeding under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 94;`
  line
  line `(zze) manner of authorisation of employer for representing in any proceeding under sub-section`
  line `(2) of section 94;`
  line
  line `(zzf) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed under the provisions of this`
  line Code.
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government shall make rules for the---`
  line
  line `(a) manner of recognition of a Trade Union or federation of Trade Unions by the Central`
  line `Government as a Central Trade Union at the Central level and the authority and the manner of`
  line `deciding dispute by it under sub-section (1) of section 27; and`
  line
  line `(b) manner of holding an enquiry under sub-section (1) of section 85.`
  line
  line `(4) All rules made under this section by the State Government shall, as soon as possible after they`
  line `are made, be laid before the State Legislature.`
  line
  line `(5) Every rule made under this section and notification issued under clause (p) of section 2, by the`
  line `Central Government shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament`
  line `while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two`
  line `or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session`
  line `or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or`
  line `notification, or both Houses agree that the rule or notification should not be made, the rule or notification`
  line `shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so,`
  line `however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done under that rule or notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (101527)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 100
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101527&sectionno=100&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government may, by notification, direct that any`
  line `power exercisable by it under this Code or rules made thereunder shall, in relation to such matters and`
  line `subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the direction, be exercisable also,---`
  line
  line `(a) where the appropriate Government is the Central Government, by such officer or authority`
  line `subordinate to the Central Government or by the State Government, or by such officer or authority`
  line `subordinate to the State Government, as may be specified in the notification;`
  line
  line `(b) where the appropriate Government is a State Government, by such officer or authority`
  line `subordinate to the State Government as may be specified in the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (101528)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 101
  title `Power to amend Schedules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101528&sectionno=101&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, add to or`
  line `alter or amend the First Schedule or the Second Schedule or the Third Schedule and on any such`
  line `notification being issued, the First Schedule or the Second Schedule or the Third Schedule, as the case`
  line `may be, shall be deemed to be amended accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification issued by the Central Government under sub-section (1) shall be laid as soon`
  line `as may be after it is made before each House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of`
  line `thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before`
  line `the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both`
  line `Houses agree in making any modification in the notification, or both Houses agree that the modification`
  line `should not be made, the notification shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no`
  line `effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done in pursuance of that notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (101529)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 102
  title `Amendment of Act 7 of 2017.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101529&sectionno=102&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `In the Finance Act, 2017, in the Eighth Schedule, against`
  line `serial number 1,---`
  line
  line `(a) in column (2), for the words "Industrial Tribunal constituted by the Central Government",`
  line `the words, brackets and figures "Industrial Tribunal constituted by the Central Government under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 44 of the Industrial Relations Code, 2020" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) in column (3), for the words and figures "The Industrial Disputes Act, 1947" (14 of 1947),`
  line `the words and figures "The Industrial Relations Code, 2020" shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (101530)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 103
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101530&sectionno=103&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Code, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such`
  line `provisions, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Code as may appear to it to be necessary for`
  line `removing the difficulty: Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of three`
  line `years from the date of commencement of this Code.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (101531)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 104
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513&sectionId=101531&sectionno=104&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00038_2020-35_1764741523513
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the notification issued under sub-section (3) of section 1 for the`
  line `commencement of any provision of this Code, the Central Government may specify that the provisions`
  line of---
  line
  line `(a) the Trade Unions Act, 1926 (16 of 1926);`
  line
  line `(b) the Industrial Employment (Standing Orders) Act, 1946 (20 of 1946); and`
  line
  line `(c) the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947),`
  line
  line `shall stand repealed with effect from the date appointed in the notification in this behalf and the`
  line `remaining provisions of the enactments referred to in clauses (a) to (c) shall remain in force till they are`
  line `repealed by like notifications in the like manner.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal under sub-section (1), anything done or any action taken under the`
  line `provisions of the enactments so repealed including any rule, regulation, notification, nomination,`
  line `appointment, order or direction made thereunder shall be deemed to have been done or taken under the`
  line `corresponding provisions of this Code and shall be in force to the extent they are not contrary to the`
  line `provisions of this Code.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (2), the provisions of section 6 of the General`
  line `Clauses Act, 1897 shall apply to the repeal of such enactments.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
